description: Appleby Real Estate have been at the forefront of the property industry in Melbourne’s east since 1963. Today, this second-generation business continues to grow and expand their services, to ensure client's maximise their return and fulfil their property ambitions. Managing Director Nick Draffin is dedicated and passionate about the company, the brand and the level of service Appleby deliver, offering an unsurpassed standard of sales and property management services. With unmatched local knowledge, formidable negotiation skills and an expansive network of industry contacts acquired over 59 years, the Appleby team is well equipped to out-perform any competition.
name: Appleby Real Estate

description:
Specialising in Residential Sales, Residential Leasing and Financial Services, Ray White Bayswater is an impressive young team of professionals who remain at the forefront of technology, marketing and training which translates to exceptional results for our clients. Dedicated to excellence the team is respected for their honesty and ethical approach, as well as their professionalism and superior customer service.

 

Situated on the fringe of the City Of Knox & City of Maroondah, these areas offer a great mix of suburban housing all of which our experienced sales & rental teams excel.

 

Ray White Bayswater is part of Australasia’s largest Real Estate Group, enhancing our marketing knowledge with a worldwide database network, and together with our local knowledge, we achieve premium results for our clients.

To enquire on how we can help you achieve you real estate goals, contact our office on 03 8727 6200.
name: Ray White Bayswater

description:
Melbourne 1 Real Estate is an independent, family owned real estate firm offering a personalized and professional real estate with full range of services to local and foreign investors, buyers. We always take pride in our business and always strive to provide both professional services and up to date knowledge to achieve the best possible results for all our clients. Honesty and respect are two qualities which we will always continue to uphold and encourage within our team environment.
Whether you’re a client or a team member, we will never let you down. Our well-informed, hard working and energetic team covers general residential real estate sales and property management, rural and special rural property sales, commercial and industrial sales, leasing and business sales.
We have many serious buyers from the overseas market.
name: Melbourne 1 Real Estate

address2: Cnr Burwood Hwy & Ferntree Gully Rd
description:
Our office was established in Ferntree Gully in mid 1970’s when the local area was expanding in leaps and bounds. The farmland was being developed into housing estates with allotments ranging from 750sqm to 1000sqm. As the population grew, businesses grew to meet the population’s demands. 1980 – 1990 was the growth decade in both residential, commercial and industrial when Ferntree Gully and the Knox area as a whole was transformed into a more modern and vibrant area.

 

Abley Real Estate joined the Professionals Real Estate Group as one of their first members’s well over 30 years ago as it was 100% Australian owned and operated. Today the group has well over 300 offices and has expanded to New Zealand, throughout South East Asia area and now looking to the United State of America. The group prides itself on its social responsibility through office contribution at local and national levels, as a key supporter to the National Breast Cancer Foundation and the Child Cancer Foundation.

 

Ray Abley is also renowned for his generosity to local sporting and community groups for junior sports for nearly 30 years.

 

Abley Real Estate Pty Ltd is known for the stability of their staff when most senior staff has been established for 15 – 20 years.

 

The office have specialised staff in the following categories.

a)            Residential Sales

b)            Residential Property Management

c)            Commercial Industrial Leasing & Sales

d)            Project Management in developments and constructions

e)            Buyers advocate service

 

You can feel confident when you appoint Abley Real Estate Pty Ltd to handle all your property needs because we have the necessary experienced staff with a minimum of 15 years experience. Our office has been voted Number One Real Estate Agency of the year in Knox on a number of occasions.
name: Abley Real Estate Pty Ltd

description:
Ray White Real Estate Ferntree Gully

Ray White Ferntree Gully enjoys a high community profile with an excellent position on Ferntree Gully Road next door to Fernwood Gym.
At Ray White Ferntree Gully we work as a team to offer maximum coverage to our clients in the sale & management of their property, enabling us to achieve excellent results for our landlords and top prices for our vendors. 
We believe that solid and ethical work practices based on continual communication with our clients is the only way to work. Much of our business comes from referrals as we aim to build our business and provide a complete Real Estate Service with honesty and integrity at its foundation.
name: Ray White Ferntree Gully

description:
Stockdale & Leggo Ferntree Gully is a leading member of the Stockdale & Leggo franchise group, Victoria’s largest, consisting of approximately 80 offices state-wide.  The Stockdale & Leggo group has been delivering real estate services to the people of Victoria for over 75 years, beginning from a single office in Glenhuntly around 1934.

The Ferntree Gully office,  as you now see it, began in 1996.  Under the careful eye of Paul Stone, Director and Tom Tsiagalos, Sales Manager, the office has grown into the market leader it is today.  The business offers “everything real estate” from Sales and Auctions to Property Management for both Residential and Commercial properties. 

Currently employing dedicated staff, the Ferntree Gully office includes a Sales Team actively listing and selling property, Residential Property Managers and a very professional team of Administration staff providing behind-the-scenes support.

Under the management of Tom Tsiagalos, his team is making its mark within this high traffic location.  With thousands of people per week visiting the Mountain Gate Shopping Centre and frontage to Burwood Highway, the exposure has provided an even greater profile for the business and more importantly our vendors.The success story of the Ferntree Gully office has been quite phenomenal. 

Not only has the office enjoyed a tremendous record over a long period, but many of our Sales and Rental staff have achieved outstanding results over the same time.  Paul Stone and Tom Tsiagalos have both established themselves within this “service hungry” industry with outstanding results over an extended period.

per
name: Stockdale & Leggo Ferntree Gully

description:
The team at Schroeder & Wallis are real estate experts within the City of Knox. We offer an unmatched level of service to all our clients no matter what your property requirements are.

 

What makes us unique is the proactive nature of our entire approach to servicing your property needs. We wear our passion for real estate on our sleeve and constantly assess and reassess the effectiveness of our campaigns with a view to improving and embracing innovation and creative thinking to guarantee outstanding results. We are highly analytical, anticipating individual needs and applying our market insights to deliver the best result for people buying, selling or leasing property.

 

The service we provide at Schroeder & Wallis is defined by passion and integrity. Combining award-winning, large-scale thinking with a commitment to tailored client care we strive to exceed expectations at all times. Above all else, our service is effective. Our specialist expertise, market knowledge and impeccable attention to detail achieve strong returns for our steady client base.
name: Schroeder & Wallis

description: Responding to the needs of an ever increasing clientele in the Maroondah area and across into Knox, Bell Real Estate are back in Montrose, covering the outer eastern suburbs of Montrose, Mt Evelyn, Lilydale, Mooroolbark and reaching back into Kilsyth, Kilsyth South, The Basin, Bayswater, Bayswater North, Croydon and even Ringwood. Displaying a commitment to Customer Service never before seen in this area, the highly trained staff working out of the Montrose office welcome the opportunity to meet and exceed your expectations in all facets of real estate. With Registered Builders, Licensed Real Estate Agents, and Property Management expertise spanning more than 40 years, with one call you’re able to access friendly valuable advice to assist you in making informed decisions regarding the improvement, selling or management of your most valuable asset. Commencing operations in the Eastern suburbs in the early 70’s Sydney Bell followed by his sons Chris and Trevor Bell and daughter Rosalie have continued a tradition of personalized service which is a hallmark of the Bell brand. Third generation agent and Sales Manager of the Montrose office Ryan Bell is a Registered Builder and renovator. Ryan has all the qualities of an exceptional team member who will achieve outstanding results for all of his clients. Your choice of agent is an important one. At Bell Real Estate guarantee of service and ethical standards are of the highest calibre. We look forward to assisting you with all of your real estate needs.
name: Bell Real Estate Montrose

description: Sue Jackson and her team take pride in offering our local area the ultimate service in real estate. Having lived in the Montrose area for some time, Sue & her team are truly passionate about Montrose & the surrounding areas. The Max Brown office in Montrose offers friendly, professional service. There is no task too big or too small for this team. Sue & her team over many, many years, have consistently achieved premium results for their clients. They are the number one agency in the local area! True success in real estate doesn't just come from selling properties it comes from being honest, understanding and loyal.
name: Max Brown - Montrose

description:
Grandstand Real Estate has been established since 2015. As an independent real estate agency, Grandstand has been servicing all areas of Melbourne. Since its establishment, Grandstand has successfully leased and/or sold properties in Melbourne sought after locations including Burwood, Camberwell, Doncaster, Ferntree Gully, Glen Waverley, Kew, Knoxfield, Malvern, Melbourne CBD, Mitcham, Mount Waverley, Ringwood, Rowville, Scoresby, South Yarra, Wantirna, Wantirna South, Wheelers Hill and so on.

We are a dynamic and multi-cultural team that strives to achieve grand outcomes for our clients with dedication and integrity. With a CLIENT-CENTRIC approach in everything we do, we actively listen to our clients’ needs, carefully plan and organize our tasks, and effectively carry out actions to deliver the best outcomes for our clients.

Conan Ong, the director of Grandstand, has more than 25 years of real estate experience. As director, Conan believes in leading by example. His career history can be measured by literally hundreds of property transactions, many of which have delivered outcomes to his clients far above their expectations. We STAND with our clients for GRAND outcomes. Together we GRAND, together we STAND.
name: Grandstand Real Estate

description:
Corporate Profile

When you list your home with Century 21 Unlimited in Ringwood East, you will be supported by a team of highly trained professionals, who are all dedicated to achieving the successful sale of your property. We recognise that your decision to sell is one of the biggest decisions in your life, so it's important to us that you receive the best customer service.

We fulfil this promise by keeping you informed. No matter which service we're providing, we will keep you up-to-date with constant communication and open dialogue. You can rely on our team, because we have all been trained - and continue to be trained - with the best industry systems on offer.

A good team is a competitive team and we at Century 21 Unlimited Ringwood East are a great team. We're always looking for ways to surpass the industry standard and consistently embrace new ideas and technology in order to serve you better.

In addition to this, you may already have the peace of mind of knowing some of our esteemed team members. This is because many of them have lived in the local area for years and knows from firsthand experience what it's like to buy and sell in the Eastern and Outer Eastern area.
name: Century 21 Unlimited

description:
Rowville's dynamic team in sales and rentals, linked with the neighbouring Barry Plant offices offers a powerful network achieving excellent results. Whether you are buying, selling or renting a home we are at your service. 

Since it's inception Barry Plant– Rowville has strived to build a professional and reputable real estate business. We pride ourselves on the reputation that we have developed.

Our aim is - 'To be professional and to provide a caring team of people who will work for you – our customer, to reach our common goal of successfully marketing real estate.'
name: Barry Plant Rowville

description:
At Ray White Rowville we work harder for our customers.

Backed with over 116 years of experience from Australasia’s largest real estate group, Ray White Rowville clients can rest assured that they have selected the right team.

Having established themselves as market leaders in the Knox area, we know firsthand what makes the area and the lifestyle attractive. What’s more, we know what motivates buyers in the local market.

Our comprehensive past client and buyer database ensures that your property is presented to more genuine buyers, to maximise the competition to buy your property. During the campaign, we use a refined set of processes that have been specifically designed to get you the best possible price for your property.

When you choose an agent at Ray White Rowville, you get the support of our full team. Our unique structure encourages all agents to work together to achieve the best price for your property. With over 1,000 offices across 11 countries, we can also connect you to buyers from all over the world. This international exposure is an added dimension no other agency can rival.

We pride ourselves on providing an exceptional level of personal and professional service to make the selling process easy and rewarding for all our clients.
name: Ray White Rowville

description: In an increasingly fast-paced world, we know that while people want the most professional efficient service, they still prize the fundamentals of honesty and integrity from real estate consultants committed to achieving their clients’ goals. That’s why at Harcourts we combine world-renowned technology, training and systems with a focus on establishing trust and respect with our clients who always remain at the centre of the process. Whether you’re buying or selling residential, commercial, rural, lifestyle, holiday rentals, land, or a new home, at Harcourts we’re proud to say we put the focus on Global. National. Local. and most importantly, You.

description:
Wantirna is one of the many suburbs to be found in the 'the most liveable City' – Knox. A vibrant and modern area nestled against the picturesque backdrop of the Dandenong Ranges. The Wantirna area continues to build on its strengths of community, business and commitment to the environment. Wantirna boasts an array of lifestyle opportunities for you and your families, including a choice of excellent private and government schools, a tertiary college, reliable public transport and the second largest shopping centre in Australia, Knox City. With over 350 specialty stores, Knox City together with Knox Ozone provides a unique shopping, entertainment, leisure and dining experience.

Brendan Murphy, Adam Sorrell and the team at Barry Plant Wantirna provide a marketing edge to vendors by placing their properties before more buyers everyday. They do this by tapping into the Melbourne wide Barry Plant network which includes working closely with the neighbouring offices of Rowville and Boronia. At Barry Plant Wantirna, we feel that being entrusted to help sell or purchase your greatest financial asset is a huge privilege and responsibility. Therefore, our ultimate aim is to make the whole experience of buying or selling real estate as enjoyable and stress free as possible every time. Occasionally someone experiences a stress free home sale by accident. We’re here to make it happen on purpose. Wantirna's dynamic teamwork, negotiation skills and their high standards of personal client attention make them the strongest force in the Knox area. "What lies before us and what lies beyond us is tiny compared to what lies within us – It's not just another property....It's your home and we’ll treat it that way"
name: Barry Plant Wantirna

description:
Cameron. is a successful and dominant company with a fine reputation and a strong team of sales, leasing and administration staff dedicated to producing outstanding results.

The cornerstone of our success has been our comprehensive knowledge and commitment to the South East Industrial/Commercial market. This knowledge developed over 40 years of hands on, on the ground dedication to a specific market place has given us the edge over national and local based competition.

Cameron. services our large base of clients from two offices based in Dandenong South and Wantirna.

Providing real estate services ranging from residential sales, property management to commercial real estate sales and lease, First National Real Estate Wantirna can help you with all your real estate needs.

At First National Real Estate Wantirna, you will always be treated as our top priority. At First National Real Estate Wantirna – we put you first.

description:
We are a progressive family owned real estate agency offering a genuinely personal level of service, while at the same time delivering the highest standard of professional real estate service and expertise.  Our company focus is on residential property management services and real estate sales within the City of Knox and surrounding Melbourne suburbs.  Our success as an ‘independent’ real estate agency has been built on the personal referral of business from past satisfied clients, tenants and landlords together with our outstanding reputation and local knowledge.

Hill Real Estate and all Hill Real Estate staff are members of the Real Estate Institute of Victoria and has suitably qualified and professionally motivated employees to enable us to guarantee a constantly high standard of personal real estate service. Our office is conveniently located on Burwood Highway, in the white terraces opposite Knox City Shopping Centre.
name: Hill Real Estate

description:
Experienced and strong performing in any market, Professionals Wantirna are highly regarded for their tenacity in achieving premium results and conscientious regard for their clients.

Established in 2001 with a commitment to excellence, Professionals Wantirna have a reputation as top performers in sales, projects, auctions, property leasing and management. We love what we do and we do it with passion, drive, excellence and enthusiasm. Referrals and repeat business from happy clients are keys to our success.

Working together as part of a 300 office network with a multi-lingual team, we employ marketing strategies that connect with people locally and internationally. We are invested in building authentic relationships with clients at every price point.

We know Knox. Our families grew up here and we view the eastern suburbs as the most liveable and desirable. We are proud to support the local community by assisting with school functions, sporting events, fetes, fundraisers and donating to the National Breast Cancer Foundation from every sale. As NBCF’s Diamond Partner, Professionals have raised over $3,000,000 and counting.

Our determination to remain customer focused is supported by our attention to detail, unrivalled knowledge, proven marketing strategies, advanced technologies, professionalism and refined negotiating skills to outpace the competition.

Our goal is to create customer happiness and help you achieve your real estate dream.
name: Professionals Wantirna

description:
Ray White Wantirna has established itself as Wantirna’s market leader in quality Real Estate services. Director Zac Clancey and the team of uncompromising Real Estate professionals ensure first class service to all Ray White Wantirna clients.

Ray White Wantirna is strategically located at the Studfield Shopping Centre where several thousand shoppers pass by the window weekly and is consistently a top ten office in the network of over 100 Ray White offices. For obligation free advice whether you are buying, selling, renting or looking to have your investment property professionally managed, call us today.

Our focus is entirely on our clients. We believe that success is built on the strength of the relationships we forge and all of our dedicated agents share our same vision and quest for excellence.

Our services include:

  • Residential land sales

description: If you're looking to put your home on the market for any reason, come to the professionals who will provide you with the highest level of client service - something you should not hope for, but expect when making such a decision. Our team here at OBrien Real Estate Wantirna will deliver top-tier professional property solutions right across the board, whether you're buying, selling, renting or leasing.
name: OBrien Real Estate Wantirna

description: With an unmatched reputation for outstanding service and results that continue to set records for the Croydon area, the dedicated team at Barry Plant are committed to making your property dealings a rewarding and hassle-free experience. As market leaders in both sales and rentals, our multi-award winning team looks forward to showing you why so many local residents rely on our professional advice.
name: Barry Plant (Croydon Sales)

description:
We bring all the contemporary elements of real estate together. The art, the science … the people, the passion!

THE ART. We are your marketing professionals. We bring your home to the market with uniqueness and creativity - tailoring an individualised marketing strategy to reach the right buyers for your home.

Our team of marketing specialists collaborate to create the most stylish results in the printed and electronic media … photography with flair, copywriting with depth, and we even offer the services of our interior designer to help with the visual presentation of your home.

And it’s all done in consultation with you. No surprises. Not a cent spent unnecessarily, or without your approval.

THE SCIENCE. Supported by the most innovative technology and training, we simply work smarter. So … our people can single-mindedly concentrate on selling your home, not chasing our tails!

AND we understand the ‘science’ of modern negotiation. Times have changed. Negotiation is not about ‘heavy-handed tactics’ or working to the ‘point of least resistance’; it’s about really understanding the needs and motivations of your potential purchasers, so that we can optimise the selling price of your home, on your behalf.

THE PEOPLE. Well, we love what we do! On a global level, Harcourts is the fastest growing real estate group in Australasia. But Harcourts Croydon is owned and operated by people just like you … we live locally; we’re families that share in the pleasures of our local parks, sporting clubs, schools, cafes. And we come together, with our years of real estate expertise, with one clear focus … to deliver an entirely fresh and energetic approach to servicing our clients. And in doing so, we bring back the old-fashioned, but never outdated, ‘service with a smile’!

THE PASSION. Passion for what you do isn’t something you can fake! Come and meet our special people; experience our instinctive desire to please our clients; enjoy the rewards of our professionalism; and share in our sales successes.
name: Harcourts Real Estate Croydon

description:
Nobody knows the Outer Eastern real estate market like Hoskins. Whether buying, selling or leasing we provide a personalised premium property experience.
 
Hoskins is a locally owned real estate agency that has specialised in the outer eastern suburbs of Melbourne for more than 60 years. With offices in Croydon and Donvale, nobody knows the current market like Hoskins. Whether buying, selling or leasing Hoskins provide a premium, personalised real estate experience.
 
As Auctioneers, Estate Agents and Rental Property Managers, Hoskins have been responsible for the development and sale of many successful residential, commercial, industrial and investment type properties.

Proud members of the Australian Real Estate Network and an accredited member of the Real Estate Institute of Victoria.

 
Specialising in the following suburbs within Manningham, Maroondah, Whitehorse and its surroundings:
  • Bayswater and Bayswater North
  • Blackburn and Blackburn North
  • Chirnside Park
  • Croydon, Croydon Hills and Croydon North
  • Doncaster East
  • Donvale
  • Heathmont
  • Kangaroo Ground
  • Kilsyth and Kilsyth South
  • Lilydale
  • Mitcham
  • Mooroolbark
  • Nunawading
  • Park Orchards
  • Ringwood, Ringwood East and Ringwood North
  • Warrandyte and Warrandyte South
  • Warranwood
  • Wonga Park
Established in 1960, when Springvale Road was just a dirt track amongst the orchards, the company grew as the new homes sprouted.

With two prominently located offices in Donvale and Croydon, Hoskins has earned an enviable reputation of integrity in the industry.
 
Dedicated to achieving the best result for each and every client ensures Hoskins is the premium agent for your property. The Hoskins approach is proven and unique.

Exceedingly proud of their points of difference, outstanding results and culture of the workplace and team, Hoskins are the premium property people.
name: Hoskins Maroondah

description: Max Brown Croydon is an integral office forming part of the highly successful Max Brown Real Estate Group. Since 1958, the Max Brown brand continues to lead the market by providing personal service, dedication, skill, experience and a team approach. Our team has every sector of the real estate market covered. From our sales team, project development team and property management team, our results speak for themselves. For all your real estate needs, please contact us for sound, reliable advice
name: Max Brown Real Estate Group

description: McGrath Croydon are proven real estate experts with years of experience and extensive knowledge of the local area. Our dedicated sales and property management team take pride in having a reputation for excellence that is unmatched in the region. The key to our success is our access to cutting edge marketing, innovative technology and now an extensive networks of interstate clients and investors spanning the east coast of Australia. With experience in a vast array of properties ranging from period homes to large family residences and apartments, our team is versatile and committed. In alignment with McGrath’s renowned six star level of customer service, we consistently provide outstanding client experiences and results.
name: McGrath Croydon

description: Methven Professionals has been established in the area for over 47 years and enjoys a reputation of honesty, integrity and market leadership. Operating out of four prominent offices, the Directors Geoff Earney and Greg Earney, head a large team of trained sales consultants and property managers, from the Mooroolbark Office together with Mark Custance and Georgia Hester at Lilydale, Brent Earney and Miles Howell at Croydon and Liam Jackson and Rose Chafer at Mt Evelyn office. If you are looking to buy, sell, rent or lease a property, call any one of our four offices today. We look forward to engaging the resources of the Methven Group to providing you with the best possible outcome.
name: Methven Professionals Croydon

description:
Ray White Croydon

It's not about Us, its about YOU!

At Ray White Croydon our focus is on listening to your needs, wants and aspirations, looking at how we can help you get to where you want, not pressuring people to sell. We really do care and understand that real estate service is not about us, it’s about you the customer.  

 

Owner and Principal of Ray White Croydon, Tamara Lloyd a fully Licensed Estate Agent, exerts a people-centric philosophy towards real estate.  Tamara offers her clients and Team the benefit of 13 years experience working across all facets of the industry including Property Management for much of her career. Inspired by the culture of the Ray White Group, likewise Tamara is committed to building and retaining a highly skilled, client-focused team and providing them with opportunities to advance their knowledge so that customers experience consistently exceptional service.  A great team gets great results.

We are real estate agents committed to offering clients a superior real estate experience whether they are looking to buy, rent or sell property in the Croydon area and surrounding Maroondah and Yarra Ranges suburbs. 

 

Property Management Experts...We value the property management division of our business as much as the sales division which is a different outlook than many real estate agencies.  Director Tamara Lloyd has a long history and much experience in the field of property management and understands the needs of both landlord and tenants.  We have a dynamic, professional and caring Property Management Team headed up by Darren Krause and Elaine Richards as Business Development Manager.

description:

We work with accountant to work out your finances with you and the best way to minimise tax on your investment property whether it is positively gear or negatively gear strategy that you had chosen.

You will find that at Cuspac Property Group we are not a typical real estate agent. We are about building relationship, whether you have a need in term of finance, in term of legal questions or construction matter, we will be there with you to find the suitable professional to come out a solution for you in your investment journey.

To many people buying or selling a property is a BIG thing, and we take this seriously. It is not just about a transaction, we care about you and want to be a partner with you in your investment journey. For us it is about making friendship. My sincere hope is that everyone that come into and have associated with us before is enriched through our meeting. 

Once you had purchased a property from us we will also help you manage it and thus give you more time to focus on the investment side of things on your next property venture.

We also speak a variety of languages from English, Mandarin, Cantonese, Malay and Indonesian.

If you feel anything that you want to chat about in term of property, please do feel free to give me a call at (03) 8678 1808, so that we can schedule a time for a tea or coffee.

 I wish you all the best in this year in your investment journey.

Sincerely,

Joshua Chong

Officer in Effective Control 

CEO

description:
WHO ARE WE?

We are just like you. We're people who live locally, raise families, interact with the local community, serve on school committees and play local sport. We are also agents and we are all about making real estate real again.

Our core belief is that you, our client, deserve only the best. The best agents, the best support staff, the best technology and the best information to make your sale the most rewarding it can be.

We also believe in fun mixed in with our hard work. We don’t take ourselves too seriously and we want you to feel comfortable in your dealings with us every step of the way. We’ll provide the coffee and all you need to bring is an open mind and a willingness to be bold and exciting. We are Market Share Property and we’re here to show you how to Buy. Sell. Better.

description:
Ray White Lilydale
 
Ray White Lilydale isn't just another real estate office. Sure, it has the premium location right in the heart of Main Street with plenty of parking right out the front. And yes, the office is beautifully presented and has the latest electronic window displays that run 24/7.
 
But where the difference comes in is with commitment and experience. As a part of the international Ray White group of more than 700 offices, Ray White Lilydale has vast array of resources available.
 
There's also the network of surrounding offices and the sort of knowledge that comes from an organisation that was founded more than 100 years ago in 1902, and prides itself on leading the way with technology and always moving with the times.
 
And then there are the people, headed up by Graham Reynolds, and Sales Manager Bruno Cascianelli. Both of them are well known identities in the area; Ray White Lilydale has a reputation for its people.
 
Highly trained and very experienced, they don't just talk real estate, they know it first hand, with all the local events, places and everything else that makes Lilydale and the Yarra Valley such a great place to live and work.
 
Call in today and meet the team from Ray White Lilydale. You'll find our high profile office at 164 Main Street Lilydale, just near the corner of Hutchinson Street and opposite the Olinda Creek Hotel.
 
Or, you may wish to phone us on 9735 5050
name: Ray White Lilydale

description:
Noel Jones Mitcham works from a beautiful 1890s building on the corner of Whitehorse and Mitcham Roads.

We have a sales team of very hard-working agents dedicated to getting you the highest price.

We have Mitcham's best Property Management team dedicated to looking after your investment property.

We speak Mandarin, Greek (well, not all of us) and a couple of other languages.

We offer a fresh, friendly and modern approach to real estate.

We get results.

Mitcham is located 20 minutes east of the CBD. Residents love the area’s tree-lined streets, open spaces and numerous bushland reserves, along with its stunning period homes and warm community spirit.

The heart of Mitcham includes some homes dating from the 19th century, but most homes were built in the 1950's and 1960s. There are also significant pockets of recent redevelopment. Capital growth has been well above the Melbourne average that past few years.

Mitcham benefits from two railway stations, namely Mitcham and Heatherdale. The area is also well serviced by an extensive bus network. A wide range of major shopping centres is easy to access - Forest Hill Chase, Eastland, The Glen, Knox City and Doncaster Shoppingtown. Mitcham Shopping Centre (just north of Mitcham station) is home to The Mitcham Hotel, Coles, specialty shops, cafes, and of course, Ray White. There are also fantastic local shopping strips such as Rangeview on Mitcham Road (with the best bakery in town).

There are a number of well regarded government and Catholic Primary and Secondary Schools and many of Melbourne's leading Private Schools in the eastern suburbs are easily accessed by public transport.

The Eastern Freeway offers excellent toll free access to the CBD and a range of inner eastern and northern suburbs and now also the southern suburbs / peninsula via Eastlink.
name: Noel Jones Mitcham

description: Providing strategic and targeted coverage for the property owners of the City of Whitehorse, from Balwyn and Burwood to Vermont and Mitcham, the PhilipWebb office in Mitcham brings together the cumulative knowledge acquired through nearly 50 years of assisting the people of Melbourne's eastern suburbs with all of their property needs. description:

First National’s success is based upon three key pillars, great people, strong leadership, and a marketing network second to none. At the end of the day our team understands that ultimately, the property business is a people business. From our fresh, friendly, renovated office, strategically located in the heart of Ringwood, the gateway to Melbourne’s outer east, we provide a dynamic service that’s responsive to our clientele’s requirements, whether selling, buying or renting is the priority.

The Ringwood team are an enthusiastic, entirely independent enterprise that extracts all the benefits provided by the reach and resources of the Australia wide First National network of over 400 offices while retaining the personal connections and family focus that only a privately run property firm can offer.

description:
Choosing An Agency Is Tough... LetUs Convince You!

1. Save Up To 65% on Agent’s Fees

We believe the industry must accept a change in the way salespeople operate being an industry leader, Changing Places have introduced a “Fixed Fee” commission structure based on the general demographic of the buyer, and the level of effort and resources required to achieve the best possible outcome for our clients, not the dollar value of your property. Our unique business model allows us to reduce running costs without sacrificing our world-class service, therefore we choose to pass this saving onto our clients saving you up to 65% on typical agent’s fees.

2. Our Centralised Database

We are in constant communication with a vast number of qualified buyers each week. These buyers are entered into our centralized data management system can opt in to automatically advised of any new property listings that match their buying criteria. Unlike traditional agency networks, all of our Area Specialists have access to this national network of buyers, effectively allowing our salespeople to market your property on a national scale putting your property in front of more buyers each week.

More Buyers + Emotionally Connected + In Competition = Premium Price

3. Our National Network of Salespeople

We employ, train and support a National network of salespeople who are experts in their field and well networked within their territory. Our training is intense so we ensure each and every Area Specialist is fully equipped and capable to effectively manage the sale of your property.

4. Our Website

In today’s world over 85% of real estate business happens online. We provide a modern platform for buyers and sellers alike to obtain up-to-date information about the property market, industry trends and tips on buying and selling residential real estate. We are continually striving to push the limits of technology.

5. A Tailored Approach

We do not favour one sale method over another. The most effective method of sale can vary from suburb to suburb, state to state. It is our approach to act in the best interest of our clients and in too many cases a property is auctioned only to leave an owner ultimately disappointed. Our Experienced Area Specialists have an intimate knowledge of their marketplace and will submit their recommendations based on factual evidence and the individual needs of the property. Fact: Out of area and passive buyers are more likely to pay a premium price for a property!

6. Personal Service

In most real estate agencies, you start out with the Principal of the firm or a Senior Salesperson, however, you ultimately find the person who ends up handing your sale is far less experienced. With Changing Places, the Area Specialist is dedicated to your property from day one and stays with you right throughout the sale process.

7. Administration Support

By providing exceptional administration support to all of our Area Specialists we eliminate a large percentage of downtime allowing our salespeople to focus the majority of their energy on achieving the best result for our clients, spending more time working with potential buyers for your property.

8. Training & Development

We believe training is key to success – all our salespeople go through an initial induction program into our brand were we teach demonstrate how our unique philosophy and commission structure can help everyday sellers who are looking for a great real estate experience. In addition to this we provide access to ongoing training events and seminars to ensure our team are fully equipped with state-of-the-art tools, knowledge, and industry best practices ensuring the very best possible outcome can be achieved for our clients.
name: Changing Places Real Estate Consultants

description:
What’s in a name? Elite is the word that guides the culture at Elite Women Real Estate (EWRE). The essential capabilities required to become a good real estate agent are strong active network connections, professional competency, firm negotiation services and familiarity with the economic variables that affect suburbs. The name EWRE means superior skills and culture.

EWRE embraces the superior values of equity and fairness and those tenets are reflected in every transaction. Nurturing skills requires a work culture that is safe to drive efficiency and effectiveness. When people are free to focus on work and are not distracted with negativity, productivity increases. Extensively reported toxic workplaces illustrates clearly the cost to business and as we celebrate International Women’s Day, EWRE reflects that safe work culture. As ‘necessity is the mother of invention’ the need for change is here.

Real estate was originally male dominated and practitioners did not fully address the needs of women other than the stereotypical functional aspects of the property. Today, women are independent decision makers and investors with interests that far exceed traditional roles. As women entered the profession the fundamentals were retained however women added diversity and representation.

EWRE agents are the property relationship builders because women champion relationships. The resources within a location, the growth of the area, the development potential, migratory behaviours and the myriad of other associations are what EWRE capitalises on for buyers and sellers. Utilising local knowledge, macro fundamentals and an e-commerce platform makes EWRE a cost-effective disrupter.

The distinctive skill set that EWRE agents offer, is derived from the inherent understanding of 52% of the population -women - clearly a point of difference. EWRE aims to service all real estate consumers and recognises the property relationship building elements that are needed. From home ownership to income supplementation and retirement planning the future of the real estate industry requires outstanding service and knowledge and that is what is in the name EWRE.
name: EWRE, Servicing Victoria and Queensland Australia

Wantirna boasts an array of lifestyle opportunities for you and your families, including a choice of excellent private and government schools, a tertiary college, reliable public transport and the second largest shopping centre in Australia, Knox City. With over 350 specialty stores, Knox City together with Knox Ozone provides a unique shopping, entertainment, leisure and dining experience.

Brendan Murphy, Adam Sorrell and the team at Barry Plant Wantirna provide a marketing edge to vendors by placing their properties before more buyers everyday. They do this by tapping into the Melbourne wide Barry Plant network which includes working closely with the neighbouring offices of Rowville and Boronia. At Barry Plant Wantirna, we feel that being entrusted to help sell or purchase your greatest financial asset is a huge privilege and responsibility. Therefore, our ultimate aim is to make the whole experience of buying or selling real estate as enjoyable and stress free as possible every time. Occasionally someone experiences a stress free home sale by accident. We’re here to make it happen on purpose. Wantirna's dynamic teamwork, negotiation skills and their high standards of personal client attention make them the strongest force in the Knox area. "What lies before us and what lies beyond us is tiny compared to what lies within us – It's not just another property....It's your home and we’ll treat it that way"

Noble Knight Real Estate, established in 1949, enjoys an enviable reputation for professionalism, integrity and outstanding results.

Our high standards have earnt us the enduring patronage of leading property owners, enabling us to become the longest established and most experienced real estate company in this sought after district.

Doug Knight is the Managing Director of Noble Knight Real Estate and has been since 1975.  The company continues to develop with his children, Catherine, Anthony and Bradley joining the dedicated team at our offices located at Lilydale and Yarra Glen.  Our team of committed staff continue to grow and strive to offer the Yarra Valley the best Real Estate service in town.
name: Noble Knight Real Estate Pty Ltd

description:
Ray White Lilydale
 
Ray White Lilydale isn't just another real estate office. Sure, it has the premium location right in the heart of Main Street with plenty of parking right out the front. And yes, the office is beautifully presented and has the latest electronic window displays that run 24/7.
 
But where the difference comes in is with commitment and experience. As a part of the international Ray White group of more than 700 offices, Ray White Lilydale has vast array of resources available.
 
There's also the network of surrounding offices and the sort of knowledge that comes from an organisation that was founded more than 100 years ago in 1902, and prides itself on leading the way with technology and always moving with the times.
 
And then there are the people, headed up by Graham Reynolds, and Sales Manager Bruno Cascianelli. Both of them are well known identities in the area; Ray White Lilydale has a reputation for its people.
 
Highly trained and very experienced, they don't just talk real estate, they know it first hand, with all the local events, places and everything else that makes Lilydale and the Yarra Valley such a great place to live and work.
 
Call in today and meet the team from Ray White Lilydale. You'll find our high profile office at 164 Main Street Lilydale, just near the corner of Hutchinson Street and opposite the Olinda Creek Hotel.
 
Or, you may wish to phone us on 9735 5050
name: Ray White Lilydale

description:
Located within the bustling centre of Lilydale, RT Edgar Yarra Valley has become a leading figure in the property market for Melbourne’s outer eastern suburbs and the Yarra Valley district, catering to a community filled with an abundance of natural beauty and fresh produce, internationally renowned restaurants, iconic wineries and vineyards, all within one hour’s drive from the city.

Established in 2002, RT Edgar Yarra Valley are rightfully proud of their long-standing reputation for delivering exceptional service and achieving outstanding results for vendors and their diverse range of properties, from historic homesteads and landed estates to heritage cottages and contemporary family homes. Their dynamic and knowledgeable team has over 70 years of combined real estate experience and is headed by well-respected estate agent Andrew Houghton.

RT Edgar Yarra Valley is set apart by its personalised and tailored approach to selling properties whilst displaying a high-level of genuine care for their clients. From Healesville to Yarra Glen, Coldstream, Gruyere, Wandin, Seville, Lilydale and beyond, RT Edgar Yarra Valley has truly earnt its reputation as the Valley’s most well-respected agency.
name: RT Edgar Yarra Valley

description:
Your Trusted Real Estate Agents in Lilydale

Here at Stockdale & Leggo, we have been one of Lilydale’s preferred real estate agents for more than 30 years, offering exceptional service that ensures your experience is second to none. Whether you’re looking to buy, sell or rent, our team of professionals are here for you every step of the way.

Offering a comprehensive range of real estate services

We know that everyone’s real estate dreams look different – which is why we cater to a range of different needs. From finding the perfect rental propery within your price range, to buying your very first home, organising strata management or selling your current property, we make sure that your experience is seamless from beginning to end.

With a team of dedicated real estate professionals guiding you every step of the way, you can feel confident knowing that you’re getting the very best service possible. Get in touch with us today to speak with someone from our friendly staff!

Helping you sell or buy the perfect property in Lilydale, Mooroolbark, Chirnside Park, Coldstream and beyond

Whether you’re purchasing a new property or gearing up to sell your current one, you’ll want to get help from a real estate professional who knows the area like the back of their hand. With our real estate agents, that’s exactly what you get. Whether you’re in Coldstream, Chirnside Park, Mooroolbark, Lilydale or the Yarra Valley, we can rouse interest in your property from serious potential buyers or find you the home of your dreams.

Whatever it is you’re looking for, we at Stockdale & Leggo can make sure that your experience is second to none – guaranteed.

Get in touch with us today

If you’re looking for real estate agents who can help you buy, sell or rent a property, look no further than Stockdale & Leggo. Servicing Lilydale and surrounding areas such as Mooroolbark, Chirnside Park, Coldstream and Yarra Valley, we are proud to be a team you can trust with your property dreams.

Call us today on 03 9735 3999 to speak with one of our friendly professionals and hear how we can help you!
name: Stockdale & Leggo Lilydale

description:
We bring all the contemporary elements of real estate together. The art, the science … the people, the passion!

THE ART. We are your marketing professionals. We bring your home to the market with uniqueness and creativity - tailoring an individualised marketing strategy to reach the right buyers for your home.

Our team of marketing specialists collaborate to create the most stylish results in the printed and electronic media … photography with flair, copywriting with depth, and we even offer the services of our interior designer to help with the visual presentation of your home.

And it’s all done in consultation with you. No surprises. Not a cent spent unnecessarily, or without your approval.

THE SCIENCE. Supported by the most innovative technology and training, we simply work smarter. So … our people can single-mindedly concentrate on selling your home, not chasing our tails!

AND we understand the ‘science’ of modern negotiation. Times have changed. Negotiation is not about ‘heavy-handed tactics’ or working to the ‘point of least resistance’; it’s about really understanding the needs and motivations of your potential purchasers, so that we can optimise the selling price of your home, on your behalf.

THE PEOPLE. Well, we love what we do! On a global level, Harcourts is the fastest growing real estate group in Australasia. But Harcourts Croydon is owned and operated by people just like you … we live locally; we’re families that share in the pleasures of our local parks, sporting clubs, schools, cafes. And we come together, with our years of real estate expertise, with one clear focus … to deliver an entirely fresh and energetic approach to servicing our clients. And in doing so, we bring back the old-fashioned, but never outdated, ‘service with a smile’!

THE PASSION. Passion for what you do isn’t something you can fake! Come and meet our special people; experience our instinctive desire to please our clients; enjoy the rewards of our professionalism; and share in our sales successes.
name: Harcourts Real Estate Croydon

description: Max Brown Croydon is an integral office forming part of the highly successful Max Brown Real Estate Group. Since 1958, the Max Brown brand continues to lead the market by providing personal service, dedication, skill, experience and a team approach. Our team has every sector of the real estate market covered. From our sales team, project development team and property management team, our results speak for themselves. For all your real estate needs, please contact us for sound, reliable advice
name: Max Brown Real Estate Group

description:
Ray White Croydon

It's not about Us, its about YOU!

At Ray White Croydon our focus is on listening to your needs, wants and aspirations, looking at how we can help you get to where you want, not pressuring people to sell. We really do care and understand that real estate service is not about us, it’s about you the customer.  

 

Owner and Principal of Ray White Croydon, Tamara Lloyd a fully Licensed Estate Agent, exerts a people-centric philosophy towards real estate.  Tamara offers her clients and Team the benefit of 13 years experience working across all facets of the industry including Property Management for much of her career. Inspired by the culture of the Ray White Group, likewise Tamara is committed to building and retaining a highly skilled, client-focused team and providing them with opportunities to advance their knowledge so that customers experience consistently exceptional service.  A great team gets great results.

We are real estate agents committed to offering clients a superior real estate experience whether they are looking to buy, rent or sell property in the Croydon area and surrounding Maroondah and Yarra Ranges suburbs. 

 

Property Management Experts...We value the property management division of our business as much as the sales division which is a different outlook than many real estate agencies.  Director Tamara Lloyd has a long history and much experience in the field of property management and understands the needs of both landlord and tenants.  We have a dynamic, professional and caring Property Management Team headed up by Darren Krause and Elaine Richards as Business Development Manager.
name: Ray White Croydon

description:
Mark Gunther – determined, enthusiastic and dedicated to local real estate with the last 23 years of which 18 of those years spent working in the Yarra Valley.  Mark has achieved high respect from the community and his peers.  His focus on Healesville, Yarra Glen and surrounding areas has contributed to many successful sales and many happy clients that keep coming back.

Mark’s outstanding approach within the real estate industry is addressed with respect, experience and diplomacy which is backed by his extensive local knowledge and dedication to Property Management and Sales in both Residential, Rural and Commercial.

Communication is an asset of Mark’s that generates a high level of client confidence.  Strong management, hard work and an astute eye for detail and accuracy have all played a large part in developing Mark’s career.

Mark looks forward to the exciting changes that are taking place in our industry and also in the beautiful region in which he has the very good fortune to work in
Mark will be pleased to assist with your queries regarding all matters real estate in the Yarra Valley.
name: First National Real Estate Mark Gunther

description: Responding to the needs of an ever increasing clientele in the Maroondah area and across into Knox, Bell Real Estate are back in Montrose, covering the outer eastern suburbs of Montrose, Mt Evelyn, Lilydale, Mooroolbark and reaching back into Kilsyth, Kilsyth South, The Basin, Bayswater, Bayswater North, Croydon and even Ringwood. Displaying a commitment to Customer Service never before seen in this area, the highly trained staff working out of the Montrose office welcome the opportunity to meet and exceed your expectations in all facets of real estate. With Registered Builders, Licensed Real Estate Agents, and Property Management expertise spanning more than 40 years, with one call you’re able to access friendly valuable advice to assist you in making informed decisions regarding the improvement, selling or management of your most valuable asset. Commencing operations in the Eastern suburbs in the early 70’s Sydney Bell followed by his sons Chris and Trevor Bell and daughter Rosalie have continued a tradition of personalized service which is a hallmark of the Bell brand. Third generation agent and Sales Manager of the Montrose office Ryan Bell is a Registered Builder and renovator. Ryan has all the qualities of an exceptional team member who will achieve outstanding results for all of his clients. Your choice of agent is an important one. At Bell Real Estate guarantee of service and ethical standards are of the highest calibre. We look forward to assisting you with all of your real estate needs.
name: Bell Real Estate Montrose

description: Sue Jackson and her team take pride in offering our local area the ultimate service in real estate. Having lived in the Montrose area for some time, Sue & her team are truly passionate about Montrose & the surrounding areas. The Max Brown office in Montrose offers friendly, professional service. There is no task too big or too small for this team. Sue & her team over many, many years, have consistently achieved premium results for their clients. They are the number one agency in the local area! True success in real estate doesn't just come from selling properties it comes from being honest, understanding and loyal.
name: Max Brown - Montrose

description:
What’s in a name? Elite is the word that guides the culture at Elite Women Real Estate (EWRE). The essential capabilities required to become a good real estate agent are strong active network connections, professional competency, firm negotiation services and familiarity with the economic variables that affect suburbs. The name EWRE means superior skills and culture.

EWRE embraces the superior values of equity and fairness and those tenets are reflected in every transaction. Nurturing skills requires a work culture that is safe to drive efficiency and effectiveness. When people are free to focus on work and are not distracted with negativity, productivity increases. Extensively reported toxic workplaces illustrates clearly the cost to business and as we celebrate International Women’s Day, EWRE reflects that safe work culture. As ‘necessity is the mother of invention’ the need for change is here.

Real estate was originally male dominated and practitioners did not fully address the needs of women other than the stereotypical functional aspects of the property. Today, women are independent decision makers and investors with interests that far exceed traditional roles. As women entered the profession the fundamentals were retained however women added diversity and representation.

EWRE agents are the property relationship builders because women champion relationships. The resources within a location, the growth of the area, the development potential, migratory behaviours and the myriad of other associations are what EWRE capitalises on for buyers and sellers. Utilising local knowledge, macro fundamentals and an e-commerce platform makes EWRE a cost-effective disrupter.

The distinctive skill set that EWRE agents offer, is derived from the inherent understanding of 52% of the population -women - clearly a point of difference. EWRE aims to service all real estate consumers and recognises the property relationship building elements that are needed. From home ownership to income supplementation and retirement planning the future of the real estate industry requires outstanding service and knowledge and that is what is in the name EWRE.
name: EWRE, Servicing Victoria and Queensland Australia

description:
Wantirna is one of the many suburbs to be found in the 'the most liveable City' – Knox. A vibrant and modern area nestled against the picturesque backdrop of the Dandenong Ranges. The Wantirna area continues to build on its strengths of community, business and commitment to the environment. Wantirna boasts an array of lifestyle opportunities for you and your families, including a choice of excellent private and government schools, a tertiary college, reliable public transport and the second largest shopping centre in Australia, Knox City. With over 350 specialty stores, Knox City together with Knox Ozone provides a unique shopping, entertainment, leisure and dining experience.

Brendan Murphy, Adam Sorrell and the team at Barry Plant Wantirna provide a marketing edge to vendors by placing their properties before more buyers everyday. They do this by tapping into the Melbourne wide Barry Plant network which includes working closely with the neighbouring offices of Rowville and Boronia. At Barry Plant Wantirna, we feel that being entrusted to help sell or purchase your greatest financial asset is a huge privilege and responsibility. Therefore, our ultimate aim is to make the whole experience of buying or selling real estate as enjoyable and stress free as possible every time. Occasionally someone experiences a stress free home sale by accident. We’re here to make it happen on purpose. Wantirna's dynamic teamwork, negotiation skills and their high standards of personal client attention make them the strongest force in the Knox area. "What lies before us and what lies beyond us is tiny compared to what lies within us – It's not just another property....It's your home and we’ll treat it that way"
name: Barry Plant Wantirna

description:
If you’re selling, we have some advice we should share with you.

Most sellers get a few agents to come and have a chat when they’re about to put their property on the market. We’d encourage you to do this. Get a few “opinions” from some local agents, talk it over if you need to, and then contact us for the facts.

In a 30 minute consultation, which will cost you exactly nothing, and is absolutely obligation free, we will explain how we are able to more accurately assess the value of your home, how we’ll get it sold in a shorter period of time, and how we’ll achieve a better property result for a far lower cost.
name: Savoy Real Estate

address2: Cnr Burwood Hwy & Ferntree Gully Rd
description:
Our office was established in Ferntree Gully in mid 1970’s when the local area was expanding in leaps and bounds. The farmland was being developed into housing estates with allotments ranging from 750sqm to 1000sqm. As the population grew, businesses grew to meet the population’s demands. 1980 – 1990 was the growth decade in both residential, commercial and industrial when Ferntree Gully and the Knox area as a whole was transformed into a more modern and vibrant area.

 

Abley Real Estate joined the Professionals Real Estate Group as one of their first members’s well over 30 years ago as it was 100% Australian owned and operated. Today the group has well over 300 offices and has expanded to New Zealand, throughout South East Asia area and now looking to the United State of America. The group prides itself on its social responsibility through office contribution at local and national levels, as a key supporter to the National Breast Cancer Foundation and the Child Cancer Foundation.

 

Ray Abley is also renowned for his generosity to local sporting and community groups for junior sports for nearly 30 years.

 

Abley Real Estate Pty Ltd is known for the stability of their staff when most senior staff has been established for 15 – 20 years.

 

The office have specialised staff in the following categories.

a)            Residential Sales

b)            Residential Property Management

c)            Commercial Industrial Leasing & Sales

d)            Project Management in developments and constructions

e)            Buyers advocate service

 

You can feel confident when you appoint Abley Real Estate Pty Ltd to handle all your property needs because we have the necessary experienced staff with a minimum of 15 years experience. Our office has been voted Number One Real Estate Agency of the year in Knox on a number of occasions.
name: Abley Real Estate Pty Ltd

description:
Ray White Real Estate Ferntree Gully

Ray White Ferntree Gully enjoys a high community profile with an excellent position on Ferntree Gully Road next door to Fernwood Gym.
At Ray White Ferntree Gully we work as a team to offer maximum coverage to our clients in the sale & management of their property, enabling us to achieve excellent results for our landlords and top prices for our vendors. 
We believe that solid and ethical work practices based on continual communication with our clients is the only way to work. Much of our business comes from referrals as we aim to build our business and provide a complete Real Estate Service with honesty and integrity at its foundation.
name: Ray White Ferntree Gully

description:
Stockdale & Leggo Ferntree Gully is a leading member of the Stockdale & Leggo franchise group, Victoria’s largest, consisting of approximately 80 offices state-wide.  The Stockdale & Leggo group has been delivering real estate services to the people of Victoria for over 75 years, beginning from a single office in Glenhuntly around 1934.

The Ferntree Gully office,  as you now see it, began in 1996.  Under the careful eye of Paul Stone, Director and Tom Tsiagalos, Sales Manager, the office has grown into the market leader it is today.  The business offers “everything real estate” from Sales and Auctions to Property Management for both Residential and Commercial properties. 

Currently employing dedicated staff, the Ferntree Gully office includes a Sales Team actively listing and selling property, Residential Property Managers and a very professional team of Administration staff providing behind-the-scenes support.

Under the management of Tom Tsiagalos, his team is making its mark within this high traffic location.  With thousands of people per week visiting the Mountain Gate Shopping Centre and frontage to Burwood Highway, the exposure has provided an even greater profile for the business and more importantly our vendors.The success story of the Ferntree Gully office has been quite phenomenal. 

Not only has the office enjoyed a tremendous record over a long period, but many of our Sales and Rental staff have achieved outstanding results over the same time.  Paul Stone and Tom Tsiagalos have both established themselves within this “service hungry” industry with outstanding results over an extended period.

per
name: Stockdale & Leggo Ferntree Gully

description: Appleby Real Estate have been at the forefront of the property industry in Melbourne’s east since 1963. Today, this second-generation business continues to grow and expand their services, to ensure client's maximise their return and fulfil their property ambitions. Managing Director Nick Draffin is dedicated and passionate about the company, the brand and the level of service Appleby deliver, offering an unsurpassed standard of sales and property management services. With unmatched local knowledge, formidable negotiation skills and an expansive network of industry contacts acquired over 59 years, the Appleby team is well equipped to out-perform any competition.
name: Appleby Real Estate

description:
Specialising in Residential Sales, Residential Leasing and Financial Services, Ray White Bayswater is an impressive young team of professionals who remain at the forefront of technology, marketing and training which translates to exceptional results for our clients. Dedicated to excellence the team is respected for their honesty and ethical approach, as well as their professionalism and superior customer service.

 

Situated on the fringe of the City Of Knox & City of Maroondah, these areas offer a great mix of suburban housing all of which our experienced sales & rental teams excel.

 

Ray White Bayswater is part of Australasia’s largest Real Estate Group, enhancing our marketing knowledge with a worldwide database network, and together with our local knowledge, we achieve premium results for our clients.

To enquire on how we can help you achieve you real estate goals, contact our office on 03 8727 6200.
name: Ray White Bayswater

description:
Boronia is one of the many suburbs to be found in the 'the most liveable City' – Knox. A vibrant and modern area nestled against the picturesque backdrop of the Dandenong Ranges. The Boronia area continues to build on its strengths of community, business and commitment to the environment.

Boronia boasts an array of lifestyle opportunities for you and your families, including a choice of excellent private and government schools, a tertiary college, reliable public transport and the second largest shopping centre in Australia, Knox City.

With over 350 specialty stores, Knox City together with Knox Ozone provides a unique shopping, entertainment, leisure and dining experience.

Mark Schroeder and the team at Barry Plant Boronia provide a marketing edge to vendors by placing their properties before more buyers everyday. They do this by tapping into the Melbourne wide Barry Plant network which includes working closely with the neighbouring offices of Rowville and Wantirna.

At Barry Plant Boronia, we feel that being entrusted to help sell or purchase your greatest financial asset is a huge privilege and responsibility. Therefore, our ultimate aim is to make the whole experience of buying or selling real estate as enjoyable and stress free as possible every time. Occasionally someone experiences a stress free home sale by accident. We’re here to make it happen on purpose.

Boronia's dynamic teamwork, negotiation skills and their high standards of personal client attention make them the strongest force in the Knox area.

"What lies before us and what lies beyond us is tiny compared to what lies within us – It's not just another property.....It's your home and we'll treat it that way"
name: Barry Plant Boronia

description:
iTRAK is moving you with the times......

iTRAK Real Estate was born from a need to offer Home Sellers a far more relevant service, one that is in line with modern technology. We provide the most efficient way to sell your home.

Our efficiency stems from an understanding of modern buyer research behavior which translates into a business model that keeps overheads and costs low

The internet has been the most powerful change to the real estate industry ever. It's changed the way buyers search for properties. It also has resulted in a massive change to just how much competition Home Sellers can attract on their home. Using a smart and professional sales strategy a well presented home can generate upwards of 100 buyer inspections in the first two weeks.

Founding Director David Stewart has established a team of like minded and experienced Agents;who can offer Home Sellers professional guidance and strategies to generate a Premium Price with the benefit of saving money. iTRAK is proud of the difference we are already making for so many Home Sellers; having already sold homes in over 50 Melbourne suburbs. We look forward to speaking to you any time; whether selling your home or taking care of your investment property.
name: Biggin & Scott Boronia
