description: Established in 1988, Ray White Noble Park has become one of the leading offices in the Ray White Network and consistently ranks as a Top 4 Victorian Office. The Team at Noble Park enjoys a high profile both within the group and locally. Our reputation in sales results and dedication to superior service has established us as the leading and most successful agent in the area. Principals Graeme Oldmeadow and Allison Grant, together with their highly trained and professional team, occupy a prominent main street office. The stunning window display offers a showcase of homes with huge exposure to busy Douglas Street. We have a significant investment in computer technology to assist us in the delivery of accurate sales information, together with prompt and effective service. The office proudly supports many community groups and sporting clubs and donates time to conduct annual charity auctions. Ray White Noble Park also has a professionally run property management and investment department. Our investors benefit from the knowledge, experience and service that we provide, which ensures the protection of your investment. We are proud of our reputation and undertake to keep you informed with the state of the market and how it affects your situation. Whether you are selling, buying, leasing or just simply seeking 'the right advice', you will benefit from our vast experience and the overall strength of the Ray White Group with over 560 offices.
name: Ray White Noble Park

description:
For over half a century, Crabtrees Real Estate have been providing Melbourne with a service built on constant success and proven experience. It’s no wonder we are regarded as one of Melbourne’s best commercial and industrial specialists. Complete property management that takes the day-to-day hassle away from you, so you can sit back and watch your investment grow from strength to strength.

When it comes to understanding the market, our broad network and solid ties with the south-eastern suburbs means our clients always get results way above their expectation. From leasing to management, all our staff are passionate about real estate, providing a professional and competitive service for all your Commercial and Industrial needs.
name: Crabtrees Real Estate Oakleigh

description:
Located just 14 kilometres south of Melbourne’s CBD, Oakleigh is rapidly modernising to become a lifestyle area with tremendous potential. With a diverse mix of properties ranging from modern townhouses to California bungalows and traditional weatherboard homes, Oakleigh offers excellent value for money for both buyers and investors.

 

A public transport hub, Oakleigh’s many bus and train services offer a quick and easy commute to the city and surrounding suburbs. With ‘The Fashion Capital’ at Chadstone on your doorstep and a burgeoning restaurant and cafe scene, Oakleigh continues to attract a new generation of professionals, young families and students.

 

The team at James Perry Property Group are long-time Oakleigh locals who’ve seen the area grow and develop over a period of more than 28 years. With a strong focus on quality service and customer

satisfaction, Perry and James Telios and their vibrant and welcoming team of property professionals offer the complete range of residential and commercial real estate services across the greater Oakleigh area including: Hughesdale, Mount Waverley, Clayton, Chadstone, Ashburton, Oakleigh South, Clarinda, and parts of Bentleigh East.

 

To speak with a local specialist, contact our Oakleigh office today or visit us at

2/64 Portman Street, Oakleigh.

P 8574 1200
name: James Perry Property Group

description:
The Oakleigh Sales and Oakleigh Rental offices form part of the Woodards South Eastern presence and provides the customary high level of personal and professional service supported by the much wider corporate presence of the Woodards organisation.

At our Oakleigh Sales Office we provide a professional team to sell any property.


"For important information on Woodards' auction policy please click on the Woodards logo  link above"
name: Woodards Oakleigh

description:
The Meadows Property Group delivers a full-service agency model, specialising in residential property development and individual listings. Our multi-disciplinary approach means we manage everything under the one roof from project marketing, portfolio management through to owner’s corporation servicing.

With over 30 years experience, managing the development of some of Melbourne’s most iconic properties, the agency prides itself on maintaining a boutique identity so that it can maximise the attention paid to its clients.

Understanding the importance of collaboration, we offer a distinct advantage through our strong client database which includes some of Melbourne’s leading developers, architects, interior designers and project managers.
name: Meadows Property Group

description:
We are known as a leading project marketing consultancy and its services are behind some Australia's most awarded and prestigious developers. Since our establishment in 2007, we have collaborated on a broad range of high and medium density developments and master-planned communities across metro and suburban regions. Our service - oriented approach ensures the needs of our clients come first. Paired with the ability to deliver outstanding results on time, every time.

At Melbournia, we are focused on delivering clients' commerical objectives by putting the shared vision and beliief in sustainable residential communities at the heart of everything we do. This stratgiec approach promotes goodwill, long term relationships and vibrant qaulity outcomes for all stakeholders. We pride ourselves in delivering highly effective project marketing solutions, offer a comprehensive scope of real estate services and apply rigorous business thinking to all projects.

The Group comprises Melbournia Developments that sits beside its full-Real Estate and developement service offer including site acquisition, commerical and residentiall project marketing and sales, project consulting, project management, asset managment and finance origation that provides lending products and services directly to business, corporate and consumers.
name: Melbournia

description:
Roger Davis Pty Ltd was established in 1971 and remains an independent family business.

OUR SALES TEAM

The skilled and expert sales team at Roger Davis offers our clients a unique selling experience where you are sure to find our service to be both professional and limitless:

We understand how important your home is to you and every listing is given personalised attention.

We work with you to ensure an effective advertising campaign is created to specifically suit your property and budget. We advertise on four Web sites as well as our own web site. We advertise each week in the local Leader newspaper being the Waverley Gazette and can produce for you quality boards and brochures.

There are no language barriers when you choose Roger Davis Pty Ltd our staff speak a range of different languages including:

  • Madarin
  • Cantonese
  • Hok Kien
  • Teo Chiev
  • Vietnamese
  • Cambodian
  • Greek

WE HAVE A STRONG SALES TEAM THAT ACHIEVES AMAZING RESULTS

The Rental Department

Is lead by a team of enthusiastic, dedicated senior property managers, our rental department has continued to grow and become one of the largest and most pro-active rental departments in Waverley.

Our Company is confident in managing residential, commercial and rural properties all over Melbourne. We take property management seriously and we provide our clients with expertise in all aspects of rental management.

Property Management is a major part of our business and we take great pride in our high standard of personalised service to our Landlords and Tenants. Regular training ensures our Department has a sharp knowledge of the current rental market.

The Goodwill created over the years where Tenants ultimately become Landlords is the basis for a lot of our business.

When associating with our family Agency, you can be assured of an efficient and professional service.
name: Roger Davis Real Estate

description:
Co-Directors and seasoned real estate professionals Adam Alexander and Grant McConnell lead a team of highly motivated and experienced real estate agents, sales consultants, business and property managers at Belle Property Dromana.

Offering unmatched levels of commitment, professionalism and marketing ingenuity, the team at Belle Property Dromana are highly regarded and well-rewarded, winning several highly sought-after industry awards in recent years.

Locals to the area, the dedicated team at Belle Property Dromana work alongside property investors, home buyers and holiday-goers in the bayside areas to achieve their property dreams.

Servicing Rosebud, Capel Sound (Rosebud West), Cape Schanck, Boneo, McCrae, Dromana, Arthurs Seat, Martha Cove and Safety Beach, Belle Property Dromana can be trusted to deliver comprehensive, strategic and empathic residential, investment and lifestyle real estate advice and services.
name: Belle Property Dromana

description:
Our business continues to provide and deliver highly professional real estate services on the Mornington Peninsula.
Our family owned independent agency pursues the highest standards of excellence to our clients.
We believe in helping people achieve their property goals, establishing good relationships and tailoring an approach that suits each and every one of our clients.
We will deliver you the best outcomes no matter the situation.
Whether it is buying, selling, management or development we look forward to you becoming one of our valued clients.
name: Bennetts Real Estate Dromana

description:
Experience & Local Knowledge Gains Results!
Prominent and highly successful Dromana Real Estate Agents, M J ROSS & CO, established in 1968 have assisted people successfully Buy, Sell & Lease property on our beautiful Mornington Peninsula, many becoming repeat Clients during our 52 years of Trading.

Results speak for themselves - our friendly and qualified Team offers professionalism, accurate advice and extensive knowledge of the local Market focusing on Dromana, Safety Beach, McCrae, Arthurs Seat and Rosebud.

Looking for a personalized approach, honesty and integrity - find our experienced team of Real Estate Professionals opposite the Dromana Pier - 5987 2800
name: MJ Ross & Co

description: Roger McMillan Real Estate is located in the main street of Dromana, opposite the Jetty.  We are ideally positioned, surrounded by cafes and bars and directly over the road from the beach.  We are a proudly independent company with a very prominent local presence.  We are open Monday to  Saturday 9am to 5pm.  Come in and discuss your real estate requirements.  You can confidently talk with us and not be disappointed.  Our aim is to build the business and to offer outstanding service to all our clients be they vendors, buyers, landlords or tenants. We take great pride in our professional approach to business, with a high level of honesty, integrity and reliability. Roger and Peter come from very successful corporate backgrounds, and are well respected within the local community.
name: Roger McMillan Real Estate

description:
Scenic Property is a boutique real estate agency on the beautiful Mornington Peninsula.

We are a team of highly-experienced professionals who are passionate about achieving incredible results for our vendors. We offer a wealth of local knowledge, years of experience, and professional in-house property styling guidance, because we know first impressions count.

We create first-class marketing campaigns utilising a carefully curated team of the Peninsula's leading photographers, graphic designers, videographers and more.

Ours is a distinctly personal, down-to-earth service. We take time to truly understand our clients and to keep you informed at every stage of your campaign.

We invite you to see why Matt's approach has seen him consistently recognised by RateMyAgent as one of the region's leading real estate agents.
name: Scenic Property

description: YPA Estate Agents Dromana provide a complete real estate service from Portsea through to Mornington and beyond. We place a high value on teamwork and service, to achieve the best results. Working closely with all of our YPA office’s around Melbourne, including the team at YPA Rye, we can promise the best service for all our client’s no matter where you live. Whether you are considering selling or renting your property, we are here to help.
name: YPA Dromana

description:
Speak to anyone who has experienced the PROCESS of buying or selling Real Estate and often their findings are a combination of stress, disappointment and ultimately compromise. One of the many goals of Briggs Shaw - Blairgowrie is to ensure your next move is a positive one.

Briggs Shaw - Blairgowrie was founded around one simple mission. 

"To deliver RESULTS that exceed our clients EXPECTATIONS". Due to our boutique nature we also feel we are "large enough to manage... and small enough to care..."

We have created 'Best Practice Systems' that provide solutions and satisfaction to your most desired wants and needs. At the foundation of our 'success system' is a philosophical shift from being a 'facilitator' presenting to a Real Estate Consumer to becoming a 'catalyst' for a Real Estate Client to find success in an industry that for decades has been inefficient and often ineffective.

"Disappointment is the difference between what a client EXPECTS and what the agent DELIVERS"

Briggs Shaw - Blairgowrie has thoroughly researched what a client requires from their agent. What they have told us is that they are craving a 'professional' who can 'listen' to their individual wants and needs and provide solutions for them!

Briggs Shaw - Blairgowrie is that professional.
name: Briggs Shaw Blairgowrie

description:
With a heritage dating back to 1938 and a reputation for excellence and innovation, Kay & Burton is a name at the forefront of Australian real estate.

For decades, the Kay & Burton brand has been synonymous with premium properties in Australia. Its record of excellence in marketing fine homes and discreet personal service has created an enviable sphere of influence in the Australian real estate industry. 

Today, Kay & Burton - which has grown to over 150 employees, with offices in South Yarra, Hawthorn, Armadale, Bayside, Flinders, Portsea & Sorrento – is attracting worldwide interest. The demand now is for excellence and exceptional service across the real estate spectrum and Kay & Burton is in a class of its own in delivering that experience. 

 

We are committed to giving you the best possible service by anticipating your expectations and ensuring that our responsibilities and promises are executed to the highest of standards. Our objective is always to obtain outstanding results for your benefit and we view your satisfaction as a measure of our ongoing success.
name: Kay & Burton Flinders

description:
Barry Plant Mornington combines over 60 years of experience in providing outstanding customer service to valued clients on the Mornington Peninsula. Each of Barry Plant Mornington’s sales agents have proven track records in delivering exceptional results; their local knowledge and outstanding negotiating ability have ensured many referrals by delighted clients.

Barry Plant Mornington not only offers Barry Plant’s guaranteed red carpet service, we can offer sellers direct access to buyers from Victoria’s number 1 real estate network, with over 80 offices. When you list with Barry Plant you are really listing with each of the offices in our network; over 1000 people working together to sell your home.

Barry Plant Mornington is not just about Sales; the same level of service is available to landlords and tenants; as a matter of fact Barry Plant won the number 1 Property Management company award for Australia in the inaugural Australian Real Estate Awards.
name: Barry Plant Mornington

description:
ConleyLUFF Real Estate Services is a boutique, independently owned agency dedicated to providing a full suite of customised real estate solutions to our Mornington Peninsula clients.

It’s our individual approach to each campaign, complemented by a flair for marketing, our experience and reputation for results that sets us apart. Having been in business since 1993, the ConleyLUFF team is dedicated to making a professional difference in real estate on the Peninsula. We believe success comes from developing strong client relationships based on mutual trust and respect. This is reflected by our many repeat clients and the strong ties we have developed with the local community.

As long-time residents and real estate professionals, our intimate knowledge of the area and its superb lifestyle benefits means we are ideally placed to market your property to the widest possible audience.
name: Conley Luff Real Estate Services
Eview Real Estate - Mornington Peninsula

description:
Based in Mornington, Victoria, the agency specialises in business, commercial and residential sales (with a particular emphasis on sales of B&B and other accommodation types), providing services to the whole of the Mornington Peninsula, Bayside and South-Eastern suburbs and regional areas.

Alan Maguire, the Agency Principal, who lives in Mornington, has a rich and varied professional background. Commencing his career as a local secondary teacher he went on to teach and manage English language and technical education projects in France, South Korea, New Caledonia, French Polynesia, East Timor, Saudi Arabia and the ten ASEAN member states of South-East Asia.

He is a fluent French and Spanish speaker and accredited translator and has 15 years experience establishing and running jewellery and B&B accommodation businesses in the Dandenong Ranges and Mornington Peninsula. He is in a perfect position to advise purchasers and vendors on appraising, selling, purchasing and marketing a small business and on preparing a B&B or residential property for sale.
name: Maguires Real Estate

description:
McEwing & Partners Real Estate is a long-established boutique real estate agency on the Mornington Peninsula. In 2000, McEwing & Partners opened its doors as a small independent agency in Mornington, with three staff. Today, the business has expanded its footprint to a second office in Mt Eliza cementing itself as one of the Mornington Peninsula's most successful real estate brands, and uniquely offering a dual office market advantage.

 

We are a bespoke full-service agency with experience across residential, commercial, and rural, at all price points. So, it doesn’t matter if you have a $500,000 or a $10,000,000 property to sell, you will enjoy the same high level of customer care and service. We’re proudly independent, meaning we have more time to focus on your property, and can deliver you more hands-on attention.

 

Our Sales and Marketing Strategies are innovative and customised to each property and requirements. We have personally handled the sales of over one billion dollars’ worth of real estate and have a hand-picked team of senior real estate professionals to provide an unrivalled level of service and advice.

 

Directors Dean Phillips, Quentin McEwing and Marcus Gollings are hands on in the day to day running of the business. The negotiation of your sale is personally handled or overseen by them, ensuring that you are in safe hands. We offer expertise in residential, commercial, and rural sales, project marketing and project management, as well as property management.

 

We strongly believe in giving back and are proud to actively support our local community through a variety events and ongoing sponsorships including Mornington Soccer Club, Mt Martha Netball Club and Davey Bay Yacht Club.
name: McEwing Partners

description:
The primary goal of the company is to help women, retirees and their 
families make informed and profitable real estate decisions. This 
ensures more money is saved and more time spent with family and loved 
ones and a great real estate experience for all is guaranteed.

With over a decade in the real estate sector of Mornington Victoria, the
 company promises to deliver quality and rewarding service to clients 
across Mornington Victoria and Australia as a whole.
name: McNeill Real Estate

description:
Welcome to NicholasLynch.

Nicholas Lynch Pty Ltd is a modern professional Real Estate Agency based on Victoria’s Mornington Peninsula that offers premium marketing backed up by first class service. We offer a unique selling experience that is achieving record sale prices.
The NicholasLynch team are extremely motivated, highly trained and enthusiastic. The Sales Consultants are also top negotiators with a exceptional understanding of the market which ensures you the best possible sale price.
NicholasLynch is a member of Real Estate Institute of Victoria (R.E.I.V).
name: Nicholas Lynch

description:
At Ray White we get you more. Here's how.

At Ray White Mornington we work harder for our customers. With the benefit of experience, we take the time to understand your needs up front. During the campaign, we use a refined set of processes that have been specifically designed to get you the best possible price for your property.

 We are the experts on the Greater Mornington area. We know firsthand what makes the area and the lifestyle attractive. What's more, we know what motivates buyers in the local market. Our comprehensive past client and buyer database ensures that your property is presented to more genuine buyers, to maximise the competition to buy your property. When you choose an agent at Ray White Mornington, you get the support of our full team. Our unique structure encourages all agents to work together to achieve the best price for your property.

As part of Australasia's largest real estate group, we can also connect you to buyers from all over the world. This international exposure is an added dimension no other agency can rival.

We pride ourselves on providing an exceptional level of personal and professional service to make the selling process easy and rewarding for all our clients.
name: Ray White Mornington

description:
Seachange Property is a unique real estate service, designed to ensure home-owners and developers maximise profit when selling or renting their homes.

 
Our aim is to achieve better sales results, in a quicker space of time, with minimum fuss. We do this by putting in the work at every stage of the sales process. We advise on and oversee the work required to reduce negatives and enhance positives to maximise value on a property, create targeted marketing, and ensure the greatest pool of potential buyers see your property's benefits, our agents open up your property to the best price in the market.
 
It takes more than qualifications to succeed in this market - that's why our team have great credentials... and more. With decades of experience as buyers, sellers, investors and developers, the team at Seachange Property are uniquely positioned to meet the needs of any vendor, at any level in the market.
 

"Seachange Property offer a full-service approach that provides the complete solution to the challenges of selling Peninsula property".

 
It costs no more to have a Mornington Peninsula Property Specialist in your corner, yet it may mean thousands of dollars difference to your selling price.
name: Seachange Property Real Estate

description:
People are at the heart of the Warlimont & Nutt philosophy – both clients and staff. The hand-picked team led by Fergus Nutt & Trent Cameron are dynamic and loyal professionals who are passionate about real estate and the local community.

Established in Mount Martha in 1952.
name: Warlimont & Nutt Pty Ltd

description:
First opened in 1930, the long established RT Edgar Portsea office has built, and most importantly maintained, its unwavering reputation as the most trusted provider of property services across the prestigious Portsea and Sorrento precincts.


After acquiring the Flinders office in 2015, Managing Director Holly Longmuir’s vision for expansion was realised in 2018, when she added the Portsea office to her rapidly growing network, followed by Sorrento and Blairgowrie.


From humble holiday homes to breathtaking beachside mansions, the team at RT Edgar Mornington Peninsula draws upon years of local knowledge, ensuring they are equally dedicated and adept in the sales, leasing and short stay management of a broad range of properties. 


With a proven track record of exceptional results, a genuine customer centric approach, and advanced technology enhancing exciting cross pollination opportunities throughout the network, RT Edgar Mornington Peninsula remains the ‘go to’ name for property expertise across the Peninsula.
name: RT Edgar Portsea

description:
Our state of the art office is positioned well amongst the hype of local and tourist activity.

Rosebud has come alive over the years offering up to date facilities, yet it still has the balance of being a relaxing seaside getaway.

At Barry Plant Rosebud, we work as a team to offer maximum coverage to our clients in the sale & management of their property, enabling us to achieve excellent results for our landlords and top prices for our vendors.

We offer you 7 day a week service, specialist private sale and accredited auction agents, a dedicated team of award winning property managers and first class administration support team members.

We believe that solid and ethical work practices based on continual communication with our clients is the only way to work. Much of our business comes from referrals as we aim to build our business and provide a complete Real Estate Service with honesty and integrity at its foundation.

At Barry Plant Rosebud, when you deal with us, you're a client for life.
name: Barry Plant Rosebud

description:
A top 10 office for Ray White Victoria, Ray White Rosebud has been established in the area for well over a decade, servicing the area of Rosebud, Mc Crae, Tootgarook and Dromana.

Whether you are selling, buying or leasing real estate in the area you can rely on the Ray White Rosebud team to always act in your best interest to achieve outstanding results. Our aim is to provide great customer service and regular communication with our clients. This has contributed to our success in residential sales and property management in the rosebud and surrounding areas.

description:

Stockdale & Leggo Dromana-Rosebud is centrally located on Point Nepean Road. description:
Crowders Real Estate brings to the Southern Peninsula a strong brand built on robust foundations.  Led by Managing Director Sam Crowder, a well known and respected agent with over 25 years experience, Crowders embodies a history of trusted family values, strong negotiation skills, respectful and informed discussions, outstanding results and renowned customer service.
 
Family owned and operated, Crowders are a team of high performing local property specialists with a vision:  to consistently deliver outstanding results via targeted, dynamic and innovative marketing campaigns with an unparalleled customer service experience.  Hard working, determined, genuine and focussed on fostering strong relationships to achieve the best outcome for every client - no matter the price point - the team are united in their values.
 
Combining leading edge systems, a powerful online and social media presence, and a connection to an extensive database built from past and present clientele, Crowders' aim is to deliver marketing campaigns designed to suit the client's requirements, locate and link buyers with sellers, and ultimately ensure their vendors achieve the best possible price.
 
Specialising in the marketing and sales of residential, coastal and lifestyle property across the entire Mornington Peninsula, Crowders have an intimate understanding of the vast contrast in dynamics between markets from Sorrento, Blairgowrie, Rye and St Andrews Beach to Tootgarook, Boneo and Rosebud.  All local residents themselves, they share a genuine passion for the region and lifetsyle it offers, and importantly, understand how a campaign should be personalised according to each property's attributes and location.
 
Whether buying or selling, you can count on Crowders for a friendly, innovative approach to real estate. Don't hesitate to call one of our area specialists for a confidential discussion on (03) 5983 3038.

Since that beginning the company has been actively involved in the growth of this magnificent region and is well recognised as a leader in Real Estate in the area.

Our objective is always to obtain outstanding results for your benefit and we view your satisfaction as a measure of our ongoing success.

A family business selling family homes...

Barry Plant Frankston is a family owned and operated business with real estate experience spanning over 25 years.

Renowned by his colleagues and clients as approachable, humble and honest, Thomas is enthusiastic and hungry to capitalize on any and every opportunity in the local marketplace, as well as delivering an amazing experience for his clients.

Being a family owned and operated business, we understand what families are looking for when selling or leasing their most important asset. description:
“No one understands a family home like a family brand’’ and there’s no stronger family brand than Ray White Frankston with a dynamic team headed by second generation family members, and backed by Australia’s strongest real estate brand.

  
Taking real estate service standards to an unprecedented level of excellence, Ray White Frankston is a family owned and operated agency that uses unwavering honesty and integrity to achieve the best sales results across Frankston and beyond.

  
Backed by the knowledge, systems and training of the Ray White group – the biggest agency in Australasia with 1000 offices across 9 countries – the team at Ray White Frankston boast the highest sales numbers per agent in the area with a large administration team ensuring service second to none, a sales team of skilled negotiators and a detailed database that promises every one of the entire team is working to source buyers and the best possible prices.

 
And with offices in Beijing and Shanghai and a partnership with the world’s largest real estate portal, Ray White has positioned itself as a premium brand in the overseas marketplace, with its website also available in Mandarin.

 
Owned and operated by John Condon and Vivienne Weston and family members including Ashley Weston, Daniel Condon, Andrew Condon and Hayley Weston, their team of more than 12 boasts more than 50 years combined experience in real estate and work together in total unity to build a database of buyers and sellers that put their clients in the hands of one of what is arguably Frankston’s best real estate agency.

 
All long time Frankston residents, the team at Ray White Frankston have an intimate knowledge and connection with the community they serve.

   
The strong administration support team ensures a service-focused agency, while the sales team are specialised negotiators.


 Heading its property management department, Hayley Weston also operates under the strictest of standards, sourcing only the best tenants for their high quality portfolio of investment properties. As a family member, Hayley has a vested interest in the success of the business.

 
 Senior sales consultant Ashley Weston says his parents’ secret to business longevity has been that they proudly operate with integrity and can hold their heads high with no regrets about every property listing and sale.


 He also draws inspiration from being part of a world-wide group that is headed by CEO Brian White, a third generation member of what is still a family company at heart.

And there is more

Us Real Estate

Where it really is all about U.

Today MPRE boasts the most experienced and proffesional staff, offering our clients the best possible service. Our staff are constantly trained by the Harcourts Group Victoria to improve our level of service to you. With advanced technology and our national and international strength MPRE Harcourts provides you with the leading edge when selling your home or managing your investment property. 

MPRE Harcourts Carrum Downs specialises in both residential sales and leasing and we look forward to assisting you our future clients in you real estate needs.

 
The Property Management Team

The Harcourts Property Management team will give you the best possible service and the most qualified advice available.

 

Our Property Management Team is dedicated to personlised customer service and strives to provide a progressive and leading property management service.

 

At Harcourts the main objective of our property management department is to maximize the income and minimise the risks associated with owning an investment property or leasing your own home.

 

The Team at Harcourts believes that choosing a property manager should be taken with much care and consideration as choosing the property itself because the return that you receive from your property is generally determined by how well it is managed.

 

Using the latest computing tools, such as EFT, tenancy searches and the Internet coupled with our vast experience the Property Management team at Harcourts can take all the worry out of the management of your investment property

description:
Choosing An Agency Is Tough... LetUs Convince You!

1. Save Up To 65% on Agent’s Fees

We believe the industry must accept a change in the way salespeople operate being an industry leader, Changing Places have introduced a “Fixed Fee” commission structure based on the general demographic of the buyer, and the level of effort and resources required to achieve the best possible outcome for our clients, not the dollar value of your property. Our unique business model allows us to reduce running costs without sacrificing our world-class service, therefore we choose to pass this saving onto our clients saving you up to 65% on typical agent’s fees.

2. Our Centralised Database

We are in constant communication with a vast number of qualified buyers each week. These buyers are entered into our centralized data management system can opt in to automatically advised of any new property listings that match their buying criteria. Unlike traditional agency networks, all of our Area Specialists have access to this national network of buyers, effectively allowing our salespeople to market your property on a national scale putting your property in front of more buyers each week.

More Buyers + Emotionally Connected + In Competition = Premium Price

3. Our National Network of Salespeople

We employ, train and support a National network of salespeople who are experts in their field and well networked within their territory. Our training is intense so we ensure each and every Area Specialist is fully equipped and capable to effectively manage the sale of your property.

4. Our Website

In today’s world over 85% of real estate business happens online. We provide a modern platform for buyers and sellers alike to obtain up-to-date information about the property market, industry trends and tips on buying and selling residential real estate. We are continually striving to push the limits of technology.

5. A Tailored Approach

We do not favour one sale method over another. The most effective method of sale can vary from suburb to suburb, state to state. It is our approach to act in the best interest of our clients and in too many cases a property is auctioned only to leave an owner ultimately disappointed. Our Experienced Area Specialists have an intimate knowledge of their marketplace and will submit their recommendations based on factual evidence and the individual needs of the property. Fact: Out of area and passive buyers are more likely to pay a premium price for a property!

6. Personal Service

In most real estate agencies, you start out with the Principal of the firm or a Senior Salesperson, however, you ultimately find the person who ends up handing your sale is far less experienced. With Changing Places, the Area Specialist is dedicated to your property from day one and stays with you right throughout the sale process.

7. Administration Support

By providing exceptional administration support to all of our Area Specialists we eliminate a large percentage of downtime allowing our salespeople to focus the majority of their energy on achieving the best result for our clients, spending more time working with potential buyers for your property.

8. Training & Development

We believe training is key to success – all our salespeople go through an initial induction program into our brand were we teach demonstrate how our unique philosophy and commission structure can help everyday sellers who are looking for a great real estate experience. In addition to this we provide access to ongoing training events and seminars to ensure our team are fully equipped with state-of-the-art tools, knowledge, and industry best practices ensuring the very best possible outcome can be achieved for our clients.
name: Changing Places Real Estate Consultants

description:
Hastings - If you've been part of it for the past 35 years, there's a name you'll know as you've driven up High Street. Tallon Estate Agents, not far from the original hardware store and milk bar. Whilst other businesses came and went, it stood firmly. Today, Tallon Estate Agents remain headed by the Tallon family, now with the Eview Group standing steadily in the wings.

It was just over three decades ago that Alfred Tallon and his wife created this family estate agency, one you could rest weary arms on, and let them do the hard work. And you knew your rental property, or sale would be taken care of in that easy, old-fashioned way.

Those same standards of tenacity and dependability have been handed down since his passing to his son, Dominic who sits proudly at the helm, maintaining and expanding the decades of work Alfred dedicated to this office. After all, Dom's lived and breathed real estate ever since he can remember, with deals being discussed by his parents over the vegies and roast at the kitchen table. Absorbing information like a sponge from his toddler times, it was natural that he take the reins one day.

Dom's reliable, dedicated and warm team specialise in residential sales, whilst Dom's work is cut out with large acquisition sales in the mix. With a background in residential sales, and a business degree with a major in accounting & management, it stands to reason that this successful Company Director handles large overseas and major Australian property deals with ease.

But what makes Dom different is what comes with heart and soul. As Director of Eview Group Tallon Estate Agents, Dom's eye watches with care each and every property that moves in and out of his office. After all, he has his father's name to uphold.

In the 1840's this village was simply a small fishing town named after its counterpart in the UK. Today, concrete slabs herald new growth in both houses and businesses that sprout into homes and jobs. Yet the values of honesty and integrity and being a person of your word are carried forward into the fabric that makes up Eview Group Tallon Estate Agents in this Western Port hub by the water, an area springing with growth at its feet.

Eview Group - Tallon Estate Agents. We're just great estate agents.

And as the work increasingly turns to technology, our internet coverage is cutting edge while other innovations allow us to conduct up to the minute laptop appraisals in the comfort of your own home using a wireless network.

The start of something big…
Established by Estelle Jacobs and Harry Lowe, the Real Estate firm Jacobs & Lowe has made history even from its beginnings in the early 1900s with Estelle Jacobs being Victoria’s first female valuer. Growing from strength to strength, the firm has added a number of businesses to its brand, most notably Warlimont & Nutt’s Mornington office, Bruce Davis and the Bennetts Property Group. As a result, Jacobs & Lowe Real Estate company boasts the largest Rental Management business on the Mornington Peninsula, alongside one of the most dynamic and experienced sales and marketing teams in Residential, Rural & Lifestyle and Commercial & Industrial property.

Its high degree of integrity and professionalism has also made Jacobs & Lowe an agency of choice for asset sales and Property Management.

Marketing options…. 
At Jacobs & Lowe our years of experience means we understand the Mornington Peninsula market, the seasonal fluctuations in buyer activity and what it takes to sell your property for the best price. Of course, not every property is the same and neither should the marketing strategy we employ for you. Your circumstances and your property's features will form the basis of a marketing strategy tailored to suit your special requirements. We take your trust seriously. Our combined team of sales, administrative and marketing staff work effectively and efficiently together to get your property into the marketplace immediately. Years of fine tuning ensures that our procedures are meticulously carried through so that nothing is overlooked.
name: Jacobs & Lowe Mornington

description:
Established in 2008 by Michelle and Kent Skoglund, Aqua Real Estate is a full-service boutique real estate agency for residential sales and lease. As the Officer in Effective Control, Michelle leads a team responsible for representing buyers and sellers locally and internationally and ensures her team delivers uncompromising customer service and exceptional results.

With passion for the Mornington Peninsula and vast local knowledge in Mount Eliza, Mornington, Mount Martha and neighbouring suburbs, we utilise an innovative marketing method and an extensive network of both local and international clients to match qualified buyers to your property.

Regardless of whether you’re selling or leasing a unit or a multi-million dollar cliff-top home, Aqua Real Estate ensures your listing activates true customer engagement and a lasting impression. With our refined presentation and exceptional customer service, Aqua Real Estate redefines real estate marketing to dynamically present your property to the widest possible audience.

As the market leader since 2008, and having sold and leased premium properties on the Mornington Peninsula across a variety of market climates, Aqua Real Estate is adept at navigating today’s market to ensure the highest possible price for your home.

Our advantage as a boutique real estate agency enables us to provide ongoing attention to detail and real customer service on a personal basis, and defines Aqua Real Estate as a brand based on trust, integrity, discretion and distinction.

description:
First opened in 1930, the long established RT Edgar Portsea office has built, and most importantly maintained, its unwavering reputation as the most trusted provider of property services across the prestigious Portsea and Sorrento precincts.

From humble holiday homes to breathtaking beachside mansions, the team at RT Edgar Mornington Peninsula draws upon years of local knowledge, ensuring they are equally dedicated and adept in the sales, leasing and short stay management of a broad range of properties. 


With a proven track record of exceptional results, a genuine customer centric approach, and advanced technology enhancing exciting cross pollination opportunities throughout the network, RT Edgar Mornington Peninsula remains the ‘go to’ name for property expertise across the Peninsula.

Ideally positioned in the centre of Mornington’s bustling shopping village, Belle Property Mornington is a team of genuine and down to earth operators; passionate about using strategic marketing to achieve impactful results for clients.

They say you shouldn’t reinvent the wheel, but if the wheel could be better, then why wouldn’t you?!

Throw your cookie cutter out the window and prepare to expect the unexpected. Harcourts Mornington is unlike any office you’ve ever seen or encountered - putting the excitement back into real estate.

Positioned at number 95 Main Street, right in the heart of all major banks, opposite the post office, next door to the news agency - and not to mention neighbouring some of Mornington’s trendiest cafes - this real estate office breaks all the moulds.

With a vision for overcoming the norm and smashing ‘glass ceilings’, the team at Harcourts Mornington have carefully curated every detail of their ground-breaking business, from the fit-out to the extraordinary lifestyle position and, of course, the hand-picked staff.

Only the very best will do - and we’re talking the wittiest, most approachable and empathetic property professionals that you’ll ever have the pleasure of doing business with. Add to that a focus on well-being and a work-from-home-inspired office; Harcourts Mornington sets the standard for new-age operations.

Supported by the latest industry technology, Harcourts’ marketing power and strategies, and their glowing reputation across the Peninsula, the team is committed to providing the best possible service to each and every person they meet.

Covering property management, sales and project development, you can be sure that whatever your real estate journey entails, the team at Harcourts Mornington are here for you.

description:
Based in Mornington, Victoria, the agency specialises in business, commercial and residential sales (with a particular emphasis on sales of B&B and other accommodation types), providing services to the whole of the Mornington Peninsula, Bayside and South-Eastern suburbs and regional areas.

Alan Maguire, the Agency Principal, who lives in Mornington, has a rich and varied professional background. Commencing his career as a local secondary teacher he went on to teach and manage English language and technical education projects in France, South Korea, New Caledonia, French Polynesia, East Timor, Saudi Arabia and the ten ASEAN member states of South-East Asia.

He is a fluent French and Spanish speaker and accredited translator and has 15 years experience establishing and running jewellery and B&B accommodation businesses in the Dandenong Ranges and Mornington Peninsula. He is in a perfect position to advise purchasers and vendors on appraising, selling, purchasing and marketing a small business and on preparing a B&B or residential property for sale.
name: Maguires Real Estate

description:
McEwing & Partners Real Estate is a long-established boutique real estate agency on the Mornington Peninsula. In 2000, McEwing & Partners opened its doors as a small independent agency in Mornington, with three staff. Today, the business has expanded its footprint to a second office in Mt Eliza cementing itself as one of the Mornington Peninsula's most successful real estate brands, and uniquely offering a dual office market advantage.

 

We are a bespoke full-service agency with experience across residential, commercial, and rural, at all price points. So, it doesn’t matter if you have a $500,000 or a $10,000,000 property to sell, you will enjoy the same high level of customer care and service. We’re proudly independent, meaning we have more time to focus on your property, and can deliver you more hands-on attention.

 

Our Sales and Marketing Strategies are innovative and customised to each property and requirements. We have personally handled the sales of over one billion dollars’ worth of real estate and have a hand-picked team of senior real estate professionals to provide an unrivalled level of service and advice.

 

Directors Dean Phillips, Quentin McEwing and Marcus Gollings are hands on in the day to day running of the business. The negotiation of your sale is personally handled or overseen by them, ensuring that you are in safe hands. We offer expertise in residential, commercial, and rural sales, project marketing and project management, as well as property management.

 

We strongly believe in giving back and are proud to actively support our local community through a variety events and ongoing sponsorships including Mornington Soccer Club, Mt Martha Netball Club and Davey Bay Yacht Club.
name: McEwing Partners

With over a decade in the real estate sector of Mornington Victoria, the

description:
Welcome to NicholasLynch.

Nicholas Lynch Pty Ltd is a modern professional Real Estate Agency based on Victoria’s Mornington Peninsula that offers premium marketing backed up by first class service. We offer a unique selling experience that is achieving record sale prices.
The NicholasLynch team are extremely motivated, highly trained and enthusiastic. The Sales Consultants are also top negotiators with a exceptional understanding of the market which ensures you the best possible sale price.
NicholasLynch is a member of Real Estate Institute of Victoria (R.E.I.V).
name: Nicholas Lynch

description:
Steve Walsh secured the One Agency licences for the Mornington Peninsula and established “One Agency - Peninsula” in 2017. Steve is a highly recommended award winning agent with experience selling residential real estate throughout the Peninsula since 2007. His strong track record is a result of his consistent, professional and personalised approach and engaging negotiation skills.

 

Our team of agents operate without a retail office base enabling them to have the day to day flexibility to provide a very personalised straight forward approach to the selling process. This assists with availability and providing constant communication with both buyers and sellers throughout the selling process.

 

Specialising in all residential property sales including rural, marina, subdivision and developments, across the entire Peninsula, the One Agency Peninsula agents are all experienced professional senior agents that through reputation and recommendation operate independently, but also combine as a powerful team to consistently achieve outcomes for their clients that meet and exceed expectations.

 

At One Agency Peninsula we work to understand both buyers and sellers property circumstances and needs so that we can deliver outcomes to satisfy both parties for their short and long term benefit.

 

We all embrace the daily lifestyle on the beautiful Mornington Peninsula and genuinely enjoy combining our passion for property, and experience and knowledge, to the task of representing each clients sale so as to obtain the best possible outcome at all times.

 

We value past clients recommendations to others that are considering selling, and we always strive to continue to receive good old fashioned word of mouth referrals.
name: One Agency Peninsula

description:
Many years of experience allow our sales people to obtain the highest possible price for your property, established by a means of world class marketing, dedication and outstanding service.

At Pingiaro Partners First National, we put you first.
name: Pingiaro Partners

description:
Uniquely yours, Radius Real Estate is a boutique network of two offices, set across the Mornington Peninsula and Kew, to work together as one to achieve the highest possible result for you, our client. Our bespoke structure allows us to utilise our buyer pool to ensure each property reaches its maximum potential, especially when selling lifestyle homes.

 

As home-grown Peninsula locals, we deeply understand property movements within our region. From the calm waters of Port Phillip Bay to the rugged surf coast of Western Port, we have you covered when it comes to our privileged coastal location. A breath of fresh air within the local market, our agents exude a vibrant passion for the industry, bringing our peerless knowledge, innovation and proactive approach to your Peninsula property experience.

 

 We live and breathe real estate, and everything we do benefits our clients. The satisfaction of helping our customers and their families move on to their next chapter or achieve their property dreams keeps us at the forefront of our industry. We are proud of our role in others' lives and work tirelessly to deliver the real estate dreams for every person that walks through our door.

 

 Our intimate knowledge of the Mornington Peninsula stems from our multi-generational life experience growing up in the region. We're ingrained in the local culture and savour every moment of the leisurely lifestyle aspects that only the Peninsula can provide. 

When it comes to buying and selling property here, Radius is front and centre. Our ‘ear to the ground' approach allows us to see what's selling, how much for and for what purpose. Whether investors are hot in the market or owner-occupiers are making the seachange, we can guide you to get the best result for any area.
name: Radius Real Estate Mornington

description:
At Ray White we get you more. Here's how.

At Ray White Mornington we work harder for our customers. With the benefit of experience, we take the time to understand your needs up front. During the campaign, we use a refined set of processes that have been specifically designed to get you the best possible price for your property.

 We are the experts on the Greater Mornington area. We know firsthand what makes the area and the lifestyle attractive. What's more, we know what motivates buyers in the local market. Our comprehensive past client and buyer database ensures that your property is presented to more genuine buyers, to maximise the competition to buy your property. When you choose an agent at Ray White Mornington, you get the support of our full team. Our unique structure encourages all agents to work together to achieve the best price for your property.

As part of Australasia's largest real estate group, we can also connect you to buyers from all over the world. This international exposure is an added dimension no other agency can rival.

We pride ourselves on providing an exceptional level of personal and professional service to make the selling process easy and rewarding for all our clients.
name: Ray White Mornington

Retirement Living by Susan Clavin Real Estate

description:
Seachange Property is a unique real estate service, designed to ensure home-owners and developers maximise profit when selling or renting their homes.

 
Our aim is to achieve better sales results, in a quicker space of time, with minimum fuss. We do this by putting in the work at every stage of the sales process. We advise on and oversee the work required to reduce negatives and enhance positives to maximise value on a property, create targeted marketing, and ensure the greatest pool of potential buyers see your property's benefits, our agents open up your property to the best price in the market.
 
It takes more than qualifications to succeed in this market - that's why our team have great credentials... and more. With decades of experience as buyers, sellers, investors and developers, the team at Seachange Property are uniquely positioned to meet the needs of any vendor, at any level in the market.
 

"Seachange Property offer a full-service approach that provides the complete solution to the challenges of selling Peninsula property".

 
It costs no more to have a Mornington Peninsula Property Specialist in your corner, yet it may mean thousands of dollars difference to your selling price.
name: Seachange Property Real Estate

description:
David Brewster, a man determined to make a better life for himself and fellow Australians. With close to 20 years in the industry as an agent, advocate, vendor and purchaser, David has been involved with over $600,000,000 worth of property transactions.

 

Over this journey he has amassed a multi-million dollar property portfolio, identifying and purchasing investment properties and development sites in key growth areas. He has experienced real estate and its benefits on all levels, and approaches the property business with absolute passion. This passion, together with a true desire to help others along their property journey, lead the creation of Buy Property Direct.

 

After a successful 11 years as Buy Property Direct, David has evolved the business into a house hold name, offering a diversification of stock across Melbourne to purchasers. To continue to expand without limits on this success within the ever changing real estate industry, David launched his new company Brewsters Property Group in 2017.

 

Brewsters Property Group is a totally independent off plan specialist, with a service offering ranging from project marketing for developers to residential sales and everything in between.
name: Brewsters Property Group

Being established top performers locally; at both a real estate franchise and an independent agency, they developed a solid understanding of the ways in which local real estate is conducted.

Their passion for real estate and ambitious goals led them to start Ash Marton Realty where today they proudly serve the Frankston and surrounding communities.

Recognised by industry leaders as one of the Mornington Peninsula's most innovative and forward thinking agents, their clear-cut approach toward real estate is breaking the traditional mold to cater for the buyers of today.

They have applied an inner city real estate approach to an outer city suburb and have created the Mornington Peninsulas first Complete Real Estate Services Company.

With aspirations in being a world class leader these values carry across both our residential sales division and our dedicated property management team. Our business is focused on building and improving its strong customer service ethic and developing a 'client for life' relationship with all of our part, current and future clients. With many of the company's staff living locally and staying with the company over numerous years, we consider ourselves a group of enthusiastic, dedicated and passionate locals who heavily involve ourselves in the immediate community. Welcome to Coastal Agents. Thank you for taking the time to get to know us a little better. In these busy times, reassurance that your property is in good hands has never been so important. 

Coastal Agents is a boutique agency with specialist local knowledge of the premium property marketplace. We specialise in marketing homes that will be acquired by a discerning buyer.

description:
The team at Eview Mount Eliza is proud to represent the leafy and attractive suburb it calls home. Eview's passion for property shows. To them, the client always comes first, and this is evident in every interaction with their experienced and professional team. Each communication is honest and informative, intending to ensure clients receive the best possible outcome and outstanding service.

Benefiting from the ideal combination of a friendly, boutique office offering high-level, personalised service with the backing of an extensive, professional, dynamic and Mornington Peninsula focused network offering training, support and most importantly a vast database of buyers who are looking for a property in the local area. Our unique "List With One, Sell With All" philosophy allows the entire network to be actively selling your property every day.

Defined by sandy beaches and a relaxed lifestyle, Mount Eliza is a friendly neighbourhood with a family-orientated community spirit. Boasting magnificent cliffs and superb native bushland, there is something for everyone seeking a spot to enjoy within this uniquely beautiful area. Mount Eliza Village will entice with its friendly locals, fantastic cafe culture and boutique shopping options, encompassing a passionate, close-knit community ambience.

The area's schools are some of the best in Victoria, with Mount Eliza North, Kunyung Primary, Mount Eliza Primary School, Toorak College and the Peninsula School all among top-performing schools in the region.

If you’re looking to put your home on the market for any reason, come to the professionals who will provide you with the highest level of client service – something you should not hope for, but expect when making such a decision. How our agents will ensure your success
Our core belief is to provide our vendors with a straightforward and yet professional guidance throughout the process from start to finish, making sure you are always completely aware of the strategies we undertake and exactly why we are doing what we’re doing. No longer will you feel like you’re in the dark about what’s happening. Because customer satisfaction is our number one concern, every single one of our agents work incredibly hard to attain the very best result for each and every vendor.

With such a huge amount of passion shared in our office for this industry as well as many years of shared experience, you can be certain that when you trust us to get the job done we will do so to the highest possible standard.

In this industry, word of mouth and sales results are the way to generate more business. As such, we strive to deliver the very best service and sales results every time.

What makes us different?
Our branch of O’Brien Real Estate has only been operational for six months now, yet in that time we have already achieved some fantastic prices for our internal and external clients. Moreover, our leading agent, Michelle Stephens, has been recognised in the top ten salespeople for the group in list and sell units in 2015. Overall, our exceptional end to end client solutions and superior customer service has a made us a preferred choice for vendors in the area. We are also fortunate to have O’Brien’s Administrator of the Year working with us, further complementing our dedicated team. Unlike our other branches, we possess accreditation’s in commercial sales and leasing, and business sales, making us the obvious choice for all your property needs.

Our ability to identify the potential in properties and embrace the changing landscape has proved instrumental to our success in this beautiful area. Whether you are a buyer or a seller of property, a local resident or a newcomer to our magic city of Frankston, we are here to listen.

Marketing

Our distinctive logo and colour toning, large presence in the Frankston Leader, head turning signs, guaranteed feature property listing on realestate.com.au, listed on domain.com.au, realestateview.com.au, homehound.com.au, yourproperty.com.au, myhome.com.au, our high profile office location and distinctive display window all ensures that we capture the attention of every potential buyer for your property.

description:
Victoria's largest regional city, Geelong is just one hour from Melbourne. It features a stunning waterfront and cultural precinct and offers a fabulous wine region on its doorstep.

Over recent years Geelong’s vast and varied attributes have come to the attention of young couples and families who are seeking the cosmopolitan lifestyle associated with Melbourne, without the traffic and higher housing costs.

With parks, gardens, beaches, the Barwon River, walking trails, great shopping and fabulous restaurants, bars and cafes, there is always something to do in Geelong.

Well serviced with excellent road and rail connections and a range of public and private schools plus its own university, Geelong provides the best of both worlds.

Geelong offers diverse living with ever changing streetscapes catering for both first home buyers right through to luxurious, up market living.

description:
Buxton Highton is centrally located within the prestigious and rapidly growing 3216 postcode district in Geelong’s outer west – a leafy, up-market enclave of predominantly large family homes.

Located by the southern banks of the beautiful Barwon River, the highly desirable 3216 district is often compared to the coveted Melbourne suburbs of Armadale and Malvern.

Taking in the suburbs of Highton, Grovedale, Wandana Heights, Belmont, Marshall and Waurn Ponds – the Highton region offers fabulous riverside parks, schools, sporting facilities, shopping and amenities, all just a 10-minute drive away from Corio Bay; making it a wonderful, family lifestyle choice.  

Buxton Highton offers an energetic and dedicated team of local real estate experts, who work in tandem with the Buxton Newtown office to provide superlative, high-quality service, marketing and specialist expertise.

Whatever your real estate requirements, Maxwell Collins’ promise to you is that we will strive to deliver maximum results.

description:
Prime Real Estate understands the fundamental importance of people in business. By hand selecting and training our people with the Prime approach, we deliver a team of enthused professionals leading the industry. We are dedicated to building successful partnerships with our clients and more importantly, passionate about going that extra distance to get you the results you deserve.

Understanding just how important your property is, Prime people are those you want to be looking after your property.

Prime Real Estate prides itself on providing a new benchmark in the level of service we provide. That is what distinctly sets us apart.

By using the latest in communication methods, effective marketing exposure and our superior industry knowledge, we are a team committed to exceeding your expectations - every time. We won’t hesitate to provide you with the Prime service - to ensure we work together to get the best possible result.

Our team recognizes communication is the key to a successful transaction. That's why, at Prime Real Estate, we tailor a relationship that suits you and your lifestyle. We understand that the little things can make the biggest difference to you. We will continue to pleasantly surprise!

It is the agents at Prime Real Estate and our unparalleled level of customer service that ensures the Prime experience delivers results that exceed all your expectations.

Our flexible and effective marketing strategies will assist you in achieving this result. Whether your potential buyer is local, national or international, you can be assured that we will adopt the right approach to achieving the best result possible.

We are constantly learning. By continually keeping ourselves in tune with the trends in your region, we ensure we know your market. This, combined with the best people and customer service, leads to Prime results.

Gina Popowicz
Director/Licensed Estate Agent
0418 594 442

Gina has established an unrivalled reputation for delivering quality service and achieving outstanding results for her clients.

I've always operated on the philosophy that you treat people as you would like to be treated yourself.

Totally dedicated and with a diligent approach to her work, Gina believes that real estate should be fun and has a natural talent for establishing relationships with her clients based on trust and respect.

The greatest compliment you can receive is recognition from your client for a job well done. The many letters and referrals I receive from satisfied clients amply illustrates this.

This caring approach Gina has established has earned her a richly deserved reputation in real estate for her ability to work closely with clients.

By delivering exceptional service through listening and responding to your needs, you'll be delighted with the results.

 

Orest Popowicz
Business Manager
0401 775 618

Orest offers the Prime Real Estate team a wealth of experience in management.

He states "I find the real estate industry competitive and exciting, similar to my previous industry in many ways and I thrive on the stimulation it brings - so I believe that I can utilize much of the knowledge I have gained"
name: Prime Real Estate

description:
PropertyOwners was born due to the lack of flexibility offered in the industry when appointing a Property Management agency. Traditionally as a landlord you either had the choice to manage the property yourself or pay an agency full fees for them to take care of it for you however this is no longer the case.

PropertyOwners clients can choose exactly what they would like us to carry out as their managing agent allowing them to only pay for what they require and save between $500-$1000 on average per year. Get in touch today to find out a little more and let us put the options back in your hands.

We are committed to getting you the best result every time.
We are VILLAROSA Real Estate.
name: Villarosa Real Estate

description:
Killen Thomas (Aust) Pty Ltd is an established Real Estate Practice whose history dates back to 1911 when it was established in New South Wales. 
Over time the company has developed a strong reputation and reliable practice in both Sydney and in Melbourne where the office was opened in 1983 covering all real estate disciplines. 

In 1992 a management buyout of Killen Thomas was effected by the current principals and directors to take the firm into todays highly competitive business environment thus creating a powerful and proactive real estate agency force.

With an enviable reputation as a full house agency, Killen Thomas have positioned themselves as an alternative to the larger and more inflexible agencies, and have achieved a pre-eminent and trustworthy respect within todays property and business community. 

At Killen Thomas, we aim to be different and establish policies which maintain the highest standards of real estate expertise and professionalism.
name: Killen Thomas Melbourne

description:
Hayden Real Estate —
Excellence in service since 1928 
Established in 1928, Hayden Real Estate has an extensive and diverse portfolio of services for residential and commercial real estate.

From sales, leasing and marketing, to property management, investment and development, Hayden Real Estate has consistently provided excellence. 

We are proud of our reputation as a dynamic, innovative and progressive organisation, with a reputation solidly built on quality service, high standards and integrity.
name: Hayden Real Estate - Anglesea

description:
Embark on a defined and considered property journey. For us, Oslo represents a new path in real estate that celebrates “just the right amount”. We live in a space of delivering what we set out to achieve, building relationships and elevating our anticipation. Ours is not an ethos of big claims and over the top movements. Ours is an ethos of nurturing, sustaining and responding to achieve success with consideration and efficiency.

Created by a collective of real estate professionals, Oslo emerged to respond to a more discerning clientele who value a level of service which is savvy, engaged and entrepreneurial.

By harnessing an intimate understanding of property within the region, we have designed an agency which develops relationships and enjoys the quiet con?dence of industry leadership. You will notice that we do not emblaze these claims on everything we do. As we see it, the strength of our process and our exceptional results naturally speak for themselves.

Oslo is an agency which elevates. At our very core is the understanding that positivity renders results and encouragement leads to attainment. When we form a relationship with a purchaser or a vendor, we become part of their story and they ours. Our process brings their property into centre focus and we embark on a collaborative journey with a shared vision of success.

We welcome you to experience what it means to work with an agency of calibre and creativity. An agency where we are not shiny, just natural. Sophisticated, not sleek. An agency which does not meet the market loudly, but moulds it quietly.

Oslo Property – defined and considered.
name: Oslo Property

description:
Since 1991, we’ve helped over 40,000 Australians make their dream of owning a home come true. We don’t just build your home, we help you with everything from arranging your finance to finding the perfect block of land. Plus, we’re backed by Australia’s leading home building group, the ABN Group, so we have the leverage to get things done.

 

Following the latest announcements from the Victorian  Government, we’re very excited to welcome groups of up to 10 visitors to our Display  Homes without an appointment. description:
Not here to play it small, Geelong Real Estate Co was born out of the desire to offer something more to the Geelong market place. With the vision for excellence, professionalism, dedication and innovation 

Geelong Real Estate Co vision: We're here not to make more money, but to make more change. To create an enviroment for staff where people are ruthlessly commited to the pursuit of perfection. 

We do not accept things the way they are. We will be run by ideas, not be hierarchy. We have a learn it all culture, not a know it all culture. 

We are obsessed with the customer experience and giving them incredible benefits.

We will be phenomenal
name: Geelong Real Estate Co.

description:
Victoria's largest regional city, Geelong is just one hour from Melbourne. It features a stunning waterfront and cultural precinct and offers a fabulous wine region on its doorstep.

Over recent years Geelong’s vast and varied attributes have come to the attention of young couples and families who are seeking the cosmopolitan lifestyle associated with Melbourne, without the traffic and higher housing costs.

With parks, gardens, beaches, the Barwon River, walking trails, great shopping and fabulous restaurants, bars and cafes, there is always something to do in Geelong.

Well serviced with excellent road and rail connections and a range of public and private schools plus its own university, Geelong provides the best of both worlds.

Geelong offers diverse living with ever changing streetscapes catering for both first home buyers right through to luxurious, up market living.
name: Hodges Geelong

description: Lynda White Real Estate is a dynamic and caring Agency; offering a boutique and bespoke range of services including residential sales, rentals, buyer and vendor advocacy. Principal, Lynda White, has been in the industry for over 20 years. Experience, longevity, efficiency and care – now that’s what every Client deserves! Call Lynda today to discuss your property needs on 0405 038 888
name: Lynda White Real Estate

description:
Buxton Highton is centrally located within the prestigious and rapidly growing 3216 postcode district in Geelong’s outer west – a leafy, up-market enclave of predominantly large family homes.

Located by the southern banks of the beautiful Barwon River, the highly desirable 3216 district is often compared to the coveted Melbourne suburbs of Armadale and Malvern.

Taking in the suburbs of Highton, Grovedale, Wandana Heights, Belmont, Marshall and Waurn Ponds – the Highton region offers fabulous riverside parks, schools, sporting facilities, shopping and amenities, all just a 10-minute drive away from Corio Bay; making it a wonderful, family lifestyle choice.  

Buxton Highton offers an energetic and dedicated team of local real estate experts, who work in tandem with the Buxton Newtown office to provide superlative, high-quality service, marketing and specialist expertise.

Geelong  VIC  3220

description:
Real Estate Geelong is a boutique agency with a team that have a very unique set of skills, knowledge and experience.

Unlike other local agents, Real Estate Geelong will only take on new clients that have been referred by our past and current clients. 

Our records speak for themself, and why we encourage anyone looking to sell to speak to call us so that we can put you in touch with our past clients. We let our clients tell you how it is rather than hear it from us.
name: Real Estate Geelong Pty Ltd

description:
Selling your business doesn't have to be hard. We are leading business brokers doing things the right way. 

What's our point of difference you ask? We do things right, and offer the highest security for our clients. We utilise trust accounting for all funds received so you know where your investment is going. We use contracts prepared by the best solicitors in Melbourne to ensure sales go through without drama or disruption to your business. We employ the strictest level of confidence for all our vendors & purchasers and assist in all aspects of the sale to ensure a smooth transition from vendor to purchaser.

Check out our website, read our blogs and our testimonials and learn what we can do for you today.

We are Melbourne-based and Victorian specialists, at Absolute good is never good enough. We are at the forefront of the industry - in knowledge, innovation, technology, and in pioneering new services.
Our mission is to remain at the forefront of business sales and to stay one step ahead with technology and the latest innovations.

Our clients are our lives, and their businesses are our lives. By maintaining the utmost ethical standards and understanding the emotional processes, our purpose is not only to achieve maximum results, but follow through to ensure a smooth transition for all parties involved.

Don't be fooled by agents claiming extraordinarily high success rates and databases of potential purchasers, the market is difficult as the economy fluctuates.

We will give you an honest evaluation based on our knowledge & experience, and we will help prepare your business for the best chance at a successful sale. We can recommend accountants & solicitors highly experienced in business sales, as well as assist buyers in organising finance.
name: Absolute Business Brokers

description:
Established in 1881, and trading as a family company since 1886, HF Richardson is one of Victoria’s oldest privately owned real estate and livestock agencies.

HF Richardson has remained a family business for more than 130 years, servicing a loyal & extensive client base from Geelong to Colac & Ballarat.

With fourth-generation family member Will Richardson now at the helm, HF Richardson employs more than 24 people and continues to support the local Geelong & rural communities.

Richardson Real Estate is the property arm of the business, managed by fifth-generation family member Matt Poustie, specialising in residential, lifestyle, rural & subdivisional property. The team service Geelong, Greater Geelong, the Surf Coast & Bellarine Peninsula via a wide array of selling methods (Auction, Private Sale, Expressions of Interest etc). 

HF Richardson’s success is built on a long history of innovation in real estate and livestock sales and a commitment to preserving important traditional values. We have moved with the times but our basic values of honesty, trust and integrity have remained.
name: HF RICHARDSON PROPERTY PTY LTD

Customer service is our first priority. It’s the promise we keep to the customer. It’s how we follow through the customer. It’s how we make them feel when they do business with us.
