description:
In 1985, John G. King began building steel frame homes in Ballarat. His vision was to pioneer a new standard of home building, using exclusively Australian made TRUECORE® steel.

In our first year of operations 35 homes were delivered. Today, JG King Homes has grown to a business that proudly builds for over 1,000 families each year. With 10 offices all around Victoria, we’re trusted by families for timeless home designs and safe, strong, highly considered builds.

Despite the recognition and accolades JG King Homes has won over the years, seeing our customers enjoy their homes is still the biggest reward of all.

We are Victoria’s largest builder of steel frame homes, but as a family-owned company, JG King Homes understands the importance of building an unrivalled home.
name: JG King Homes

description:
Based in the South Melbourne, an inner city suburb just 2 kilometres away from the Melbourne CBD, Accrue Real Estate is a specialist investment property company.

The team of professionals at Accrue Real Estate are client focussed. The use their expertise to provide meaningful property market insights to their clients, with the aim to assist them in the decisions they make around the purchase of property. With a long history, Accrue has also focused on developing relationships with clients, and since launching their service they have had the pleasure of being able to assist well over one thousand customers.


Many people talk about property investment but not all go on to actually purchase something. There are many reasons for this and at Accrue Real Estate we work with our clients throughout the while process, and our years of experience are able to provide them with the information they need to decide if the purchase of property is right for them. Working with Accrue Real Estate provides clients with the confidence to take control of the process. Our insights allow clients to make informed decisions to best meet their property goals.


The Accrue Real Estate team believe that successful relationships are only built if the process allows for the clients to make the key decisions. For this reason, the time spent building includes a component of education so that the client can learn from the experience of the Accrue team. Accrue share their market insights, their suburb data and provide their clients with the knowledge they need to develop their skills to operate within the real estate market. Accrue clients are confident in knowing the Accrue team will support them throughout every stage of their property purchase. In this way, Accrue clients are able to make the necessary strategic decisions to create or further develop their property portfolio.


Developing client relationships requires more than just providing information. Just as important as talking is listening. Accrue listen to what their clients have to say. Some arrive with a fully developed property plan, others want to find out more before they set their goals. At Accrue, our team our expert in helping clients reach their goals regardless of the stage they are at when they arrive at our door. Key to our success in this the relationships we have developed with a range of other experts. 


These professionals provide services to Accrue Real Estate clients to ensure that they are happy with the decisions they make and that they are comfortable that property purchase is right for them. Accrue has developed relationships with accountants, financial planners, brokers and property managers so that our clients are supported throughout the entire course of any property acquisition. This means our clients are able to be thorough in their financial decision making but can also explore other options, such as investment through a Self-Managed Super Funds (SMSF).

Accrue Real Estate provides a Property Short Listing Service that is second-to-none. The properties we introduce our clients to have been subject to in-depth research, so we know they are suitable to meet our client’s goals. Our clients our shown multiple properties to ensure that the final decision is theirs. Written reports outline the reasons each property is suitable; the data included in these reports are based on the Accrue team’s expertise in the Melbourne property market. There’s nothing like first-hand experience, however, and for this reason we take our clients to see each property, giving them a tour at a time that suits them. Seeing all the properties makes the decision making process easier and allows our clients to be more comfortable with their final choice of property. 


Having chosen the property, our clients can then relax knowing that the Accrue Real Estate team will then do all the hard work. Negotiating the price and settlement date and completing all the necessary paperwork are part of the Accrue service. All of this is then personalised and presented to our clients to sign. Accrue Real Estate are also able to acquaint their clients with qualified and proficient property managers. This means that any investment property can be secured with tenants who have been screened and are reliable. 

Accrue Real Estate aim to build successful client relationships. This means that once the property is purchased, we continue to work for our clients. This includes monitoring the property location and reporting information back to the client in an annual meeting. This also allows our client to consider their position and whether they want to make further property purchases.

One of the keys to the success of Accrue Real Estate client relationships is that we have listened to the feedback of the hundreds of clients, allowing us to better tailor the experience of our clients. Our clients arrive with a wide range of experience, skills and investment goals. The Accrue team are aware of the most frequently asked questions and many of the concerns clients have about property investment. 


The service provided by Accrue Real Estate to our clients helps take the concern and anxiety out of any property purchase and can provide them with the means to meet financial dreams and goals. The expertise of the Accrue Real Estate team makes investment possible for all our clients, regardless of their level of skill or knowledge. The relationships we build with client helps ensure that potential pitfalls can be avoided.
name: Accrue Real Estate

description:
In May of 2011, the Reliance group was inaugurated through the opening of our first branch, Reliance Werribee, where the mission and vision for the company began. In the heart of the suburb, our enthusiastic team is equipped with the expertise and knowledge of their local area, specialising solely in the Wyndham housing market. Led by Director, Sunil Kumar, and Senior Sales Manager, Vik Monga, the team of 12 is renowned for their dedication, exceptional customer service and impeccable history of successful results since 2011.

Reliance Real Estate Werribee delivers a localised, boutique style service powered by the strength and extended reach of the Reliance network. Through the use of unique, sophisticated and innovative property marketing campaigns, sales strategies and management, we stand apart from our competitors with a commitment to constantly finding new ways to connect more buyers with sellers. Moreover, our multi-office combined database of over 90,000 contacts allows this results-driven team to easily identify and engage the most relevant buyers for your property from a large local pool as well as further afield. More buyers signifies greater competition, which can only lead to a phenomenal result.

The client relationship is highly valued by each of the team members at Reliance Werribee, who promise to utilise their extensive local knowledge and negotiation skills to get you the best sales outcome. Our experienced sales professionals are invested in building genuine relationships with buyers throughout the process, ensuring the end result is one esteemed by all parties involved. Additionally, weekly team meetings allow recent updates relating to a property campaign to be communicated amongst the team which in turn presents extra resources to connect buyers with the right property.

With the median growth of Werribee reaching almost 60% in the past 5 years, our team knows what it takes and is more than capable of keeping up with the market trends through their professionalism, tenacity and desire to revolutionise the modern real estate market. No task is too much for our agents and our support team is just as devoted to making any encounter with the real estate industry a positive one. We understand the value of family and the importance of a secure home, which is why our sales team and property management team are renowned for their dedication to their clients in fulfilling their dreams.

Reliance Real Estate Werribee is privileged to have strong ties to our local communities, and we work hard to give back, both at individual and group levels. Reliance Werribee proudly provides sponsorship and fundraising support to many local schools, sporting groups and associated community groups through the Reliance Foundation, as well as involvement in various charity events, raising awareness around numerous
social justice and health related matters.
name: RELIANCE REAL ESTATE TARNEIT

description:
A family based business, which commenced trading in Torquay in 1952, we proudly celebrate over 65 years of service to the real estate industry.  As the first full time real estate office in Torquay, our knowledge of the local market is unprecedented and the permanency of our business; an indication of our ongoing success.

Our staff are all qualified and well versed in their roles.  The sales team share over 80 years combined experience in real estate sales, each keen, versatile and honest.  We at McCartney Real Estate are proud to have played an active role in the history of Torquay.  We are keen to further those activities, assist you with your real estate aspirations, and offer you a personal professional and informed approach with your endeavours.

description:
Victoria's largest regional city, Geelong is just one hour from Melbourne. It features a stunning waterfront and cultural precinct and offers a fabulous wine region on its doorstep.

Over recent years Geelong’s vast and varied attributes have come to the attention of young couples and families who are seeking the cosmopolitan lifestyle associated with Melbourne, without the traffic and higher housing costs.

With parks, gardens, beaches, the Barwon River, walking trails, great shopping and fabulous restaurants, bars and cafes, there is always something to do in Geelong.

Well serviced with excellent road and rail connections and a range of public and private schools plus its own university, Geelong provides the best of both worlds.

Geelong offers diverse living with ever changing streetscapes catering for both first home buyers right through to luxurious, up market living.

description:
Established in 1881, and trading as a family company since 1886, HF Richardson is one of Victoria’s oldest privately owned real estate and livestock agencies.

HF Richardson has remained a family business for more than 130 years, servicing a loyal & extensive client base from Geelong to Colac & Ballarat.

With fourth-generation family member Will Richardson now at the helm, HF Richardson employs more than 24 people and continues to support the local Geelong & rural communities.

Richardson Real Estate is the property arm of the business, managed by fifth-generation family member Matt Poustie, specialising in residential, lifestyle, rural & subdivisional property. The team service Geelong, Greater Geelong, the Surf Coast & Bellarine Peninsula via a wide array of selling methods (Auction, Private Sale, Expressions of Interest etc). 

HF Richardson’s success is built on a long history of innovation in real estate and livestock sales and a commitment to preserving important traditional values. We have moved with the times but our basic values of honesty, trust and integrity have remained.
name: HF RICHARDSON PROPERTY PTY LTD

name: Condie & Co Real Estate

description:
Servicing all of Geelong's Lifestyle & Rural Areas, Bellarine Peninsula, Surf Coast, Barrabool and more......

You’re in Safe Hands With Peter Lindeman

Delivering Exceptional Results for Over 20 Years 

If you’re thinking of selling a Rural or Lifestyle acreage property

on the Bellarine, the Barwon or beyond then think Peter Lindeman.

Peter spent 20 years managing farms before jumping the fence to

sell them; and over the last 20 years he’s helped clients achieve

extraordinary results, more often than not surpassing their

expectations. Why not let Peter show you how he can help

you achieve an outstanding result for your property.
name: Elders Real Estate Geelong

description:
Established in 1881, and trading as a family company since 1886, HF Richardson is one of Victoria’s oldest privately owned real estate and livestock agencies.

HF Richardson has remained a family business for more than 130 years, servicing a loyal & extensive client base from Geelong to Colac & Ballarat.

With fourth-generation family member Will Richardson now at the helm, HF Richardson employs more than 24 people and continues to support the local Geelong & rural communities.

Richardson Real Estate is the property arm of the business, managed by fifth-generation family member Matt Poustie, specialising in residential, lifestyle, rural & subdivisional property. The team service Geelong, Greater Geelong, the Surf Coast & Bellarine Peninsula via a wide array of selling methods (Auction, Private Sale, Expressions of Interest etc). 

HF Richardson’s success is built on a long history of innovation in real estate and livestock sales and a commitment to preserving important traditional values. We have moved with the times but our basic values of honesty, trust and integrity have remained.
name: HF RICHARDSON PROPERTY PTY LTD

description:
Jodie Bliss Real Estate has been born from an idea that real estate is about service, a service based on honesty, integrity and trust. A small boutique office in the heart of Newtown Jodie Bliss Real Estate wants to build a respected reputation built on hard work, not from buying someone else’s name.

Our core value of remaining low volume to enable us to provide a high quality service, our strength lies in the fact the sales team you deal with own the company.

All our campaigns are built from the ground up ensuring every property, no matter what its size or value, is given the best possible opportunity to achieve the best possible result.

Jodie has a vision to create a service driven real estate company unlike any other in the Geelong area. What motivates this  highly driven individual is the exciting opportunity to shape and create an organisation that excels at every level.

While our main focus is selling residential property, we want the process of buying and selling to be an exciting, seamless experience for you.

Her reputation is built on three main principals:

Integrity: you can rely on our advice

Trust: we market properties effectively and you know your property is in safe hands

Honesty: we value our clients and express this in our relationships

We are an independent boutique agency that is locally owned and operated by Jodie.

With the owner of the company being the person you deal with personally and having an active role in sales, you can be sure that you are getting the skills and personal service that is deserved.

We strive to go that extra mile and pride ourselves with outstanding results that go beyond our client’s expectations, not just empty promises.

We value our clients and understand that good working relationships need care and consideration. As we move forward as a successful company we will continue to be enthusiastic, optimistic and grateful for your support.

Contact Jodie Bliss and let me win your trust.
name: Jodie Bliss Real Estate

description:
Whitford is an exciting boutique real estate company in Geelong. 

Our vision is to offer outstanding customer service, superior marketing methods and advanced negotiation skills to deliver a stress free, top of the market result for our clients. We will preserve our independent, boutique status, only handling quality property in our selected areas.
name: Whitford

description:
Wilsons is an independent real estate agency established in 1972 specialising in the Geelong and region’s real estate market.

We are not about being the biggest but we are about being the best. Quality is at the heart of everything we do from our people, selling methods, property advice to marketing strategies.

The green diamond, a symbol for quality, has represented our real estate business from the beginning. In the early years as Bodey Wilson & McKewan to the present day Wilsons, a family owned and managed company.
name: Wilsons

description:
Embark on a defined and considered property journey. For us, Oslo represents a new path in real estate that celebrates “just the right amount”. We live in a space of delivering what we set out to achieve, building relationships and elevating our anticipation. Ours is not an ethos of big claims and over the top movements. Ours is an ethos of nurturing, sustaining and responding to achieve success with consideration and efficiency.

Created by a collective of real estate professionals, Oslo emerged to respond to a more discerning clientele who value a level of service which is savvy, engaged and entrepreneurial.

By harnessing an intimate understanding of property within the region, we have designed an agency which develops relationships and enjoys the quiet con?dence of industry leadership. You will notice that we do not emblaze these claims on everything we do. As we see it, the strength of our process and our exceptional results naturally speak for themselves.

Oslo is an agency which elevates. At our very core is the understanding that positivity renders results and encouragement leads to attainment. When we form a relationship with a purchaser or a vendor, we become part of their story and they ours. Our process brings their property into centre focus and we embark on a collaborative journey with a shared vision of success.

We welcome you to experience what it means to work with an agency of calibre and creativity. An agency where we are not shiny, just natural. Sophisticated, not sleek. An agency which does not meet the market loudly, but moulds it quietly.

Oslo Property – defined and considered.
name: Oslo Property

description:
Barry Plant Geelong is the real estate specialist for Geelong and surrounds. The Barry Plant Group is the number one real estate group for sales in Australia (Real Estate Business magazine 2012) - an award based on our sales efficiency. In fact it was determined that, on average, a Barry Plant sales person sells twice as many properties per year as the average sales person from other agencies.

The award winning team at Barry Plant Geelong (sales) are dedicated to providing Red Carpet Service to every client every time. We have the skills and commitment to make selling your home a rewarding experience. By implementing well targeted marketing and tapping into the vast Barry Plant network, we'll cast a wide net to find the right buyer for your property. Or if you are looking to purchase, we'll work just as hard to help you find the right property to suit your needs.

Located in the heart of Geelong CBD, with a brand new office providing state of the art advertising along with traditional customer service, we’re sure the experience will be right for you.

In addition to the 30 years combined experience between the directors alone, Barry Plant Geelong (Sales) looks for every opportunity to please clients on all levels with the best training for their staff to ensure that you only get ‘Your Red Carpet Experience’.

“...at the end of a transaction, our aim is to have all parties walk away ecstatic, that’s when we know we’ve done a great job...”

So whatever your requirement please call us on 03 5221 4011 to experience our Red Carpet Service.
name: Barry Plant - Geelong

description:
Established last century Compton Green Geelong is your premier real estate company for service, advice and results. With an experienced team of professionals available 24/7 to help with your real estate needs, we specialise in residential and commercial sales and leasing. Our sales team are here to guide you through every aspect of the sale and buying process while our property management team, with decades of experience in leasing and management can handle every aspect of leasing for you.

We see our role as providing you with a professional experience whether buying, selling or leasing property. Our long history of providing quality service to Geelong and its surrounding suburbs speaks for itself as a reminder that those who provide consistent service, advice and results last the test of time. Contact our office today and experience our service for yourself. Our office is centrally located in Moorabool Street in Geelong's CBD, with easy access and parking.
name: Compton Green Geelong

description:
Eastwood Andrews are located in central Geelong and offer a refreshing approach to real estate sales and property management.  Both Directors Nicole and Amanda have over 30 years combined experience in the real estate industry.  Having worked at other companies, they recognised the need for a more personalised and caring approach in selling and leasing properties and interacting with clients, understanding the transaction is about the client and their particular needs not about the agent and their profile.  At Eastwood Andrews, we understand selling a family home or a main asset is  an important transaction in everyone's life and an outstanding result and stress-free sale is paramount.  We are a vendor's agent  who recognise our vendors as individual  people with different needs and expectations and always aim to achieve the best possible outcome.  Every property and every vendor is treated with the same level of importance.

Our goal is to be recognised as 'your agent', now and in the future, to form a trusting and highly respected relationship so when you or your family or friends  need anything to do with real estate, it is Eastwood Andrews thay you phone without a second thought.
name: Eastwood Andrews

description:
PropertyOwners was born due to the lack of flexibility offered in the industry when appointing a Property Management agency. Traditionally as a landlord you either had the choice to manage the property yourself or pay an agency full fees for them to take care of it for you however this is no longer the case.

PropertyOwners clients can choose exactly what they would like us to carry out as their managing agent allowing them to only pay for what they require and save between $500-$1000 on average per year. Get in touch today to find out a little more and let us put the options back in your hands.
name: propertyowners.com.au

description:
Trusted. Responsive. Meticulous.

We are relationship builders. 
We are professional marketers. 
We are buyer nurturers.
We are committed to getting you the best result every time.
We are VILLAROSA Real Estate.
name: Villarosa Real Estate

description:
Not here to play it small, Geelong Real Estate Co was born out of the desire to offer something more to the Geelong market place. With the vision for excellence, professionalism, dedication and innovation 

Geelong Real Estate Co vision: We're here not to make more money, but to make more change. To create an enviroment for staff where people are ruthlessly commited to the pursuit of perfection. 

We do not accept things the way they are. We will be run by ideas, not be hierarchy. We have a learn it all culture, not a know it all culture. 

We are obsessed with the customer experience and giving them incredible benefits.

We will be phenomenal
name: Geelong Real Estate Co.

description:
Geelong Residential is a locally owned business specialising is the sales, leasing and management of all types of residential property assets.

Geelong Residential, together with co-branded Geelong Commercial has extensive experiance in managing, leasing and selling residential, retail, industrial, office and development properties throughout the Geelong region.
name: Geelong Residential

description:
You’ve managed to get your foot on the property investment ladder, whether you’ve grown your portfolio, leasing your family home, built a brand new investment or renovated. What now? Where do you start?

Renting out your investment property can seem daunting, but it doesn’t have to be. Luxe Property Management Geelong has experience whatever the situation and will handle the entire process for you. In fact, we may already have an extensive list of pre-qualified singles and couples, ready to move into a property just like yours. When you have a new tenant, we will look after inspections and all of the legalities associated with leasing a property.

Find out what our property management service covers
name: Luxepm Geelong

description:
Real Estate Geelong is a boutique agency with a team that have a very unique set of skills, knowledge and experience.

Unlike other local agents, Real Estate Geelong will only take on new clients that have been referred by our past and current clients. 

Our records speak for themself, and why we encourage anyone looking to sell to speak to call us so that we can put you in touch with our past clients. We let our clients tell you how it is rather than hear it from us.
name: Real Estate Geelong Pty Ltd

description: Belle Property Geelong has been the driving force of exceptional marketing and sales expertise in this highly sought-after Victorian region. Established as a local boutique agency, they have a community approach to their work and an ambition to help as many people as possible with their real estate needs while making the experience the best in the industry.
name: Belle Property Geelong

description:
At Harcourts North Geelong we are a local family business & a company built on family values, honesty, results & service. Combine our local knowledge & industry expertise with the global & national resources that Harcourts International offer & the result is an agency that aims to deliver superior real estate solutions every single time.

Harcourts North Geelong offer a full range of services. We specialise in Residential Sales, Property Management services & Commercial Sales & Leasing through NAI Harcourts. Our agency has over 88 yrs of combined experience in sales & a wealth of local knowledge, first making our mark in the northern suburbs of Geelong in 1991 as North Geelong Real Estate
name: Harcourts North Geelong

description: Mayfield Real estate is an estate agent based in North Geelong, Victoria. Our complete knowledge of the Geelong real estate market includes residential home sales, property management, commercial leasing, project marketing and land subdivision sales. Although we are based in North Geelong we list properties across the Greater Geelong region including Geelong West, Herne Hill, Manifold Heights, Hamlyn Heights, Newtown, Geelong, East Geelong, Belmont, Highton, Corio, Batesford and more.
name: Mayfield Real Estate

description:
Welcome to Ray White

Opening the Lara Office in May 2008, Ray White Lara is locally owned and operated by Principal Jo Boothroyd. Offering comprehensive Real Estate services from Residential Home Sales, Property Investment Management, Body Corporate Management, Free Property Appraisals, Auctions, Commercial Sales, Rural Sales, an in-house Conveyancing service, (Connect Conveyancing) & in-house Loan Market finance broker, Ray White Lara are your innovative Real Estate Agents for the Northern Suburbs of Geelong.

At Ray White Lara we strive to provide the best possible service for our clients, this means having only the most experienced and dedicated team.

Having local residents as a part of our team provides Ray White Lara with exceptional local knowledge & above all, the vast experience any client would appreciate.
name: Ray White Lara

description:
The first Buxton office was established by the company's founder John Robert
Buxton in South Melbourne in 1861.

Since then, Buxton has expanded to become one of Victoria's  premier real
estate groups, with a network of offices across many key inner-suburban and
bayside locations, including Greater Geelong and Regional Victoria. We have
established a proud reputation for our reliability, integrity and our
ability to achieve the highest prices for our sellers and landlords.

Buxton Ballarat is operated by directors Mark Nunn & Ben Halsall, who have
both been very successful agents in the industry locally since 2003.

With a focus on high impact marketing, customer service and good outcomes,
the team at Buxton Ballarat is setting a new benchmark in the local real
estate industry.

For further information on how Buxton can assist you with your real estate
requirements, please contact our office today on 03 5331 4544.
name: Buxton Ballarat

description:
With a desire to provide a more personal, definitive service, this business heralds in a new identity and progressive approach to Real Estate service.

The company’s vision of a specialist firm being client service focus, has since materialised into one of the area’s most respected and prominent agencies.

Caine Property has grown to include amongst its services residential sales, executive leasing and property management, project management and prestige property sales.

Based on the principles of ‘magnificent service, delivered with care’, Caine Property prides itself on the dynamics of the agency and their ability to deliver comprehensive, personalised service.

Caine Property is actively involved in the local community, schools and social events and ardently supports local business.

Fiercely proud of the local environment, the Caine Property team regularly promotes the fantastic standard of living in Ballarat and the surrounding area  have to offer and will continue providing their unique service to local families and individuals.
name: Caine Property

description:
Harcourts Ballarat Putting The Spotlight On Ballarat To The World.

Harcourts Ballarat have redefined the role of the real estate company – from a simple sales focus to the expert marketing and negotiating capability today’s sellers require.  No two properties are the same – so each marketing proposal must be specifically tailored.  

 

In an increasingly fast-paced world, we know that while people want the most professional efficient service, they still prize the fundamentals of honesty and integrity from Real Estate consultants committed to achieving their clients’ goals.

That’s why at Harcourts Ballarat we combine world-renowned technology, training and systems with a focus on establishing trust and respect with our clients who always remain at the centre of the process.

Through our enormous office network of over 780 offices in 8 countries, we deliver more buyers to you, which creates a competitive market place, achieving higher prices for your real estate. 

Harcourts Ballarat putting the focus on GLOBAL, NATIONAL, LOCAL and most importantly YOU!
name: Harcourts Ballarat

description: PRDnationwide Ballarat Real Estate provides a variety of services including property research, residential sales, commercial sales, leasing, property and asset management, financial services and land marketing.
name: PRDnationwide Ballarat

description:
RE/MAX Real Estate Solutions, Ballarat opened in 2005 and was the first RE/MAX office to open in Victoria. RE/MAX was established 40 years ago in the USA and now has 6481 offices in 97 countries Worldwide, being the largest Real Estate Franchise in the World. 

Our office founded by Geoff Sullivan, who has lived and worked in Ballarat all his life and has over 30 years real estate experience, having a sound real estate and local knowledge. RE/MAX Real Estate Solutions has developed an experienced team, with the vision to continue to expand and develop.  Fostering the motto “Outstanding Agents...Outstanding Results”.

We offer the service and expertise to assist you with all your real estate requirements.

Contact our friendly staff at our office at 619 Sturt Street, Ballarat or phone (03) 53 334425.  We are the SOLUTION to all your real estate needs.
name: RE/MAX  Real Estate Solutions - Ballarat

description: Trevor Petrie Real Estate Pty. Ltd. is located at 621 Sturt Street, Ballarat. A Real Estate office in Ballarat since 1988. With parking at the front door, the position in the main street is ideal for vendors, purchasers, landlords and tenants alike. A modern office, with a wonderful bright, effective window display. As a vendor or landlord your property is displayed 24 hours a day. Feel welcome to call into our office at anytime.
name: Trevor Petrie Real Estate

description: The Barry Plant Group is Victoria’s most successful real estate group, selling more properties than any other network out of their 70+ offices
name: Barry Plant Ballarat

description:
Biggin & Scott Ballarat works with total conviction in achieving amazing results that are commensurate with the superb quality of advertising & high calibre of sales & leasing consultants you engage. Our clients can rest assured that at every stage we are willing to go above and beyond to achieve the best possible  result.

The measure of our success is in our capacity to utilize the power of our brand to provide unfair advantage to all who engage us. Our brand is synonymous with superb homes and truly benchmark results. For this reason, we also attract the best buyers and tenants in the market.

Our approach is  enthusiastic and professional. We continually research, train and develop ourselves and our team to maintain our passion and remain the best in our region.

Achieving you a result you are thrilled with, underpins everything we do at Biggin & Scott Ballarat. If you are selling in the Ballarat region give us a call. WE DELIVER RESULTS!
name: Biggin & Scott Ballarat & Creswick

The award-winning team at Jellis Craig Ballarat represents best-in-class real estate sales and property management services.

Driven by a commitment to innovation, a client-oriented approach and unparalleled market insight, Jellis Craig Ballarat consistently delivers superior outcomes to property owners throughout the city and surrounding regions.

Led by two of Ballarat’s most esteemed property professionals, Directors Tim Valpied and Tony Douglass, Jellis Craig Ballarat stands apart from its competitors through premium service and a respectful yet results-focused culture.

Known for their extensive local knowledge and skillful negotiations, Jellis Craig Ballarat’s property professionals bring deep market expertise to every relationship. The team’s record of outstanding results extends across all localities and property types including prestige homes, lifestyle properties, developments and land.

A hard-working, collaborative ethos and shared commitment to client success help Jellis Craig Ballarat to exceed expectations. Backed by the strategic presence of the wider Jellis Craig network, Jellis Craig Ballarat engages with more buyers, more often, showcasing Ballarat’s varied real estate offering to a diverse audience locally, in Melbourne and overseas.

Clients who choose Jellis Craig Ballarat can be confident they are engaging the area’s most trusted, motivated and experienced real estate team.

description:
Licensed Estate Agents & Auctioneers. Member REIV


Just like the city in which the business operates, Bendigo Real Estate is proud, progressive and faces an exciting future.

Having been established for over 20 years, with a focus on continually looking for new and innovative ways to market and promote your property, along with a dedicated sales team, bringing to the industry a refreshing vibrancy; an unparalleled energy and a commitment to offering the ultimate in service and understanding.

Bendigo Real Estate is a member of the prestigious statewide governing body of the real estate industry, the REIV. Also, to maintain fluency with modern real estate market trends, the staff regularly attend training courses and relevant real estate agent seminars.

The team’s approach is simple – they offer vendors and buyers the respect that they deserve when making one of life’s biggest transactions, whilst endeavouring to get the best possible price for every property.

They know and understand the emotion that comes with that and offer integrity, sensitivity and discretion at all times.

Not only when you list your property with Bendigo Real Estate do you  draw on the team’s extensive local knowledge, but you also tap into our resources with LMPA network including their systems and procedure and our ongoing training with them as well as the REIV & RER network to keep up with new innovations and practices in property management.

Add to that a marketing program that includes access to four internet sites, the award winning Bendigo Weekly and you can be assured your property is in the right hands.

The Bendigo Real Estate team has worked hard to ensure they have brought together a group of professional people striving for excellence – now let them work for you.
name: Bendigo Real Estate

Priority1 Property is a team who are passionate about providing exceptional and professional service to our Vendors, Investors, Landlords and Tenants. Whether you are a purchaser, seller, property owner or a tenant, we strive to remove the stress that comes with selling or renting.

Providing Residential and Commercial Sales and Property Management, you can rest assured knowing that 100% of our time is dedicated to managing your property needs, or ensuring you are comfortable in your home.

Servicing the Greater Bendigo region and surrounding rural areas, we sell and manage properties in Central Bendigo and also the rural areas such as the Lockwood area and the towns of Tarnagulla, Bridgewater, Inglewood, Serpentine, Goornong, Elmore, Dunolly and Wedderburn. We service the shires of Buloke, Loddon and Bendigo through our office network.

Our expert Real Estate Agents and Property Managers have over 100 years of experience between them and will be pleased to assist past and new clients with all of their real estate needs.

Call or email us today.! At Priority1 you are Priority1.

description:
Professionals Bendigo is owned and operated by the highly respected locals Terry Clarke, Jacinta McIvor and Danny Clarke. With over 70 years combined experience between them in the real estate industry, they have been operating their own agency in Bendigo for 30 years. We're family people, and it's a family business, says Terry, with around 30 years operating our real estate business in Bendigo, and the surrounding district. Our success is built on integrity and open communication. We have fun too.

Professionals' agents strive to achieve the best possible results for their clients, in the shortest possible time. The key to this is ongoing industry training that ensures your Professionals' agent has up-to-the minute knowledge of legislation, best practice, and your local property market.

The Professionals is also a modern company with a firm belief that each industry has environmental and social responsibilities. These beliefs are so well aligned with those of Terry, Jacinta and Danny, that joining forces with the Professionals was an easy choice to make.

Each year the Professionals group raise a significant amount of money for vital research undertaken by the National Breast Cancer Foundation of Australia and the Child Cancer Foundation in New Zealand. The Professionals group raise this money through direct contribution, fundraising, charity events and through a percentage of every property sale.

Many of you may already know that Jacinta and her husband generously open their home each year for the Girls Night In, a fabulous night of fun and fond memories of those lost to breast cancer.

Buying, selling, residential or commercial, property management of just some good advice. Trust your Professionals agent - they take care of the little things, because it's the little things that count.

Professionals Bendigo
84 Mitchell Street
Bendigo VIC 3550
Ph: 03 5442 1122
Fax: 03 5442 1992

description:
Craig Webster commenced in the industry in 2001 in Bendigo and made the decision to start Webster Real Estate Bendigo Pty Ltd in 2012. With a fresh approach specialising in Real Estate sales, auctions, and property management, we’re small, offer personalised service, and we’re proudly passionate that we live and work in Greater Bendigo.

Vision Statement

To establish Webster Real Estate as the most refered local agency in Greater Bendigo. Working together to achieve yours and our dreams.

Mission Statement

To combine innovative marketing with quality customer service at competitive prices to provide the best Real Estate experience for our customers.

Why List Your Property with Webster Real Estate Bendigo Pty Ltd? 

Choosing an agency to sell your home is a vital decision and can be difficult. All agencies do similar things, list property, market property, negotiate sale. We all use similar tools
to achieve this for sale boards, photography, brochures, internet listings, inspections, ofi’s etc. So what sets the best agents apart? Work ethic – we do the simple repetitive things well and always put in 100% Self Confidence – we believe in our systems and procedures, along with hard work, will achieve our clients the best results. Results - successful agents get results, and achieve their client goals. Determination – we strive to achieve mastery in Real Estate and be the best agency not the biggest. Passion – We are proud and passionate about Bendigo real estate. Personable – Don’t get caught in the numbers ensure that you receive the service & marketing you require. Negotiation – the most important skill of a successful real estate agent. Communication – No dealing with a PA, direct agent contact. If you are considering selling your property call us today for a free quote and utilize experience in the local area since 2001.

A fresh Approach to Property Management!

Webster Real Estate Bendigo is now offering all their clients property management services. Craig Webster, with his hands-on approach to management conducted considerable research before deciding on the policy, procedures and software to operate their new service to landlords and prospective tenants. “The number one complaint in our industry has always been communication or lack thereof, whether buying, selling, or leasing real estate,” Craig said. “With our systems in place we can deliver better communications, as we can access our system anytime, anywhere with no more doubling up or “I will get back to you once I am back in the office” excuses. Webster Real Estate Bendigo can also assist investors with finding suitable property
name: Webster Real Estate Bendigo

description:
Located just 120 kilometres (an easy 90 minute drive or train ride) north of Melbourne, Castlemaine is the heart of Victoria's historic goldfields and is now at the centre of a new gold rush of metropolitan buyers fleeing Melbourne in search of a more relaxed lifestyle without sacrificing the cultural attractions and quality of services the city provides. What can you find here? Clean fresh air, rolling farmland, historic architecture, safe leafy streets, internationally famous gardens, including the grand Botanical Garden, vineyards and wineries, art galleries, a wide range of restaurants (from the posh to the populist), golf courses and sporting facilities, heritage sites, thousands of acres of pristine bush filled with wildlife - and a lot of friendly people who love their area.
Unlike most of the regional centres in Australia that appeal to tourists, weekenders and holiday makers, Castlemaine is supported by strong local industry. This solid business base generates considerable prosperity, confidence and pride. It also gives the area an atmosphere of substance and authenticity. Add to these benefits efficient healthcare, education and transport facilities, and you have something unique - not just in Victoria but in all Australia and perhaps the world. A big claim for a small town. Put it to the test.
name: Castlemaine Property Group Pty Ltd

description:
Business brokers and advisers who specialise in helping business owners

 

This simple philosophy embodies everything we do at Rinnovate. From our coaching modules to our business sales directory, our buyer advocacy service to our business advice consultations.


Our commercial approach is all about increasing the value of your business – whether you want to sell it, grow it or simply increase your sales and profits.  There are very few business consulting or business broker firms that have such expertise and hands on experience assisting business owners to buy and sell. 

Our team brings three key aspects to the important process of the sale of a business:

Expertise: we have the in-house expertise to properly analyse and value a business prior to offering it for sale, and then to manage all aspects of the sale, including the purchaser’s due diligence process, a financier’s review process, and managing third party stakeholders such as franchisors and landlords.  We also screen the business to evaluate if it is ‘sale-ready’ and, if not, recommend exactly what you need to do to get it there.

Energy: we devote rigorous attention to follow-up of leads; we bring enthusiasm to the sale process; and we bring a determination to persist until we achieve a sale.

Ethics: we don’t just chase a quick sale to the detriment of our vendors; we won’t take on listings where something is “not quite right”; and we bring the highest standards of professional conduct to the business sale process. 


On behalf of our vendors, we prepare a detailed information and marketing presentation to provide to potential buyers. Our advertising and marketing activities are wide-ranging, including use of social media, other electronic and print media, and direct marketing.

We screen buyer enquiries prior to providing any information about a business, to ensure the potential buyer is a suitable candidate for the acquisition. Strict confidentiality procedures are in place for protection of sensitive vendor information. 

In summary, we manage the entire sale process for the vendor, providing them a seamless and hassle-free sale experience, while also providing guidance and assistance to prospective buyers throughout the transaction.
name: NAI Harcourts Rinnovate Business Brokers

description:
Bendigo Best Agents is a real estate agency that aims not only to sell properties fairly but to also help improve the real estate lives of people we connect with every day. We put accountability and fairness back into real estate with our ‘Fair Go Fee’ guarantee.

We’re the only agency in Bendigo prepared to offer our clients a written advice guarantee. We stand by the marketing and price advice we provide clients because we know what works. Homeowners choose to list their properties with us for these important reasons:


RESULTS – Speed is the key to achieving a great sales result for your home. Each clients reason for selling is different, so we personalised our strategy to suit each situation. Our logical advice accelerates the sales process enabling us to reduce the selling time. Our Fair Go Fee Guarantee sold time is way under the Bendigo Markets current average selling time around 60 days.


COMMUNICATION – Engage us to sell your home and you’ll receive superior expertise, unwavering commitment and fair and logical advice. We understand that selling your home can be a challenging prospect, but we’ll guide you every step of the way.  


PROOF OF SUCCESS – We gauge our success, not just on the sales price and days on market but, on what sellers and home buyers say about their experience after the sale is complete. Read our reviews and you’ll find a high number of repeat clients whom we’ve helped.


With nearly 30 years in the Bendigo property market, it’s our local market knowledge, personal network and qualified database of active buyers that gives us a clear competitive advantage.


Our greatest endorsement, however, comes from the repeat number of past clients who have engaged us to help them sell time and again, alongside clients that have referred us to friends and family. This tells a much greater story about our level of service than anything else.


From helping a young couple sell their first home, to supporting retirees as they navigate the challenges of downsizing, the most important element to us in every sale is the people. Listening to each client's unique needs and then strategising the best approach to ensure we get an outstanding result – that’s what drives us!
name: Mark O'Shea Realty
McKean McGregor Real Estate Pty Ltd

description:
Why Choose Us?

Delighted clients:

We aim to provide our clients a rewarding experience with our real estate agency.

Proven results:

As real estate agents, we have achieved excellent sales and benchmark results right across all price ranges. From $250,000 - $12,750,000. We regularly sell properties that other real estate agents have failed to sell.

Client Care:

We ensure that everything we do is in the best interests of our clients. This includes constantly honing our negotiation skills as a real estate agent, not disclosing offers to ensure we get the highest price possible, and not underselling the property just to make the sale.

Fair fees and charges:

We offer a fair commission rate and the advertising costs are significantly lower than nearly all of our real estate competitors. We believe that most real estate agents charge too much and deliver too little.

We genuinely do have buyers:

Our real estate agency has detailed records of all buyers that contact us regarding properties for sale.

Accurate market assessments:

If you want to know the true value of your property, ask us. You will receive an honest and accurate assessment of properties for sale based on recent sales and comparable properties completely free of charge and obligation.

Expertise:

We have been selling properties for more than 15 years, so we know the business of real estate, the current market and more than likely, the buyer for your home or property for sale.

Available 7 days:

Your property is always for sale when your real estate agent is easy to contact. We work in the evenings and on Sundays, and regularly receive great feedback from buyers that find other real estate agents hard to catch.

If you are thinking of buying and/or selling real estate, you should call us on: 03 9296 2044 or Scott McCormick 0409 216 465 anytime.

description:
Bendigo Best Agents is a real estate agency that aims not only to sell properties fairly but to also help improve the real estate lives of people we connect with every day. We put accountability and fairness back into real estate with our ‘Fair Go Fee’ guarantee.

We’re the only agency in Bendigo prepared to offer our clients a written advice guarantee. We stand by the marketing and price advice we provide clients because we know what works. Homeowners choose to list their properties with us for these important reasons:


RESULTS – Speed is the key to achieving a great sales result for your home. Each clients reason for selling is different, so we personalised our strategy to suit each situation. Our logical advice accelerates the sales process enabling us to reduce the selling time. Our Fair Go Fee Guarantee sold time is way under the Bendigo Markets current average selling time around 60 days.


COMMUNICATION – Engage us to sell your home and you’ll receive superior expertise, unwavering commitment and fair and logical advice. We understand that selling your home can be a challenging prospect, but we’ll guide you every step of the way.  


PROOF OF SUCCESS – We gauge our success, not just on the sales price and days on market but, on what sellers and home buyers say about their experience after the sale is complete. Read our reviews and you’ll find a high number of repeat clients whom we’ve helped.


With nearly 30 years in the Bendigo property market, it’s our local market knowledge, personal network and qualified database of active buyers that gives us a clear competitive advantage.


Our greatest endorsement, however, comes from the repeat number of past clients who have engaged us to help them sell time and again, alongside clients that have referred us to friends and family. This tells a much greater story about our level of service than anything else.


From helping a young couple sell their first home, to supporting retirees as they navigate the challenges of downsizing, the most important element to us in every sale is the people. Listening to each client's unique needs and then strategising the best approach to ensure we get an outstanding result – that’s what drives us!
name: Mark O'Shea Realty

Having been established for over 20 years, with a focus on continually looking for new and innovative ways to market and promote your property, along with a dedicated sales team, bringing to the industry a refreshing vibrancy; an unparalleled energy and a commitment to offering the ultimate in service and understanding.

They know and understand the emotion that comes with that and offer integrity, sensitivity and discretion at all times.

Not only when you list your property with Bendigo Real Estate do you  draw on the team’s extensive local knowledge, but you also tap into our resources with LMPA network including their systems and procedure and our ongoing training with them as well as the REIV & RER network to keep up with new innovations and practices in property management.

Ray White is a family business that owes its success to an unwavering focus on customer service, which has underpinned its operations for over 110 years. From humble beginnings, Ray White is now Australasia’s largest real estate group. When you choose Ray White Bendigo, you have access to Ray White’s worldwide network, the latest industry information, the support of an international real estate brand, plus the local knowledge and enthusiasm of our Bendigo team.

Directors Brent and Rory work hard to recruit the right people, professionals who are committed to a culture of excellence and integrity. Each team member upholds a high standard of ethics and professionalism, and ensure that you feel like part of the Ray White family. The positive relationships they develop are evident through constant repeat business and glowing referrals, all greatly appreciated by the team. They are passionate about the local Bendigo community, specialising in charity auctions and giving back wherever possible to local schools and organisations.

Ray White Bendigo understand the importance of you feeling supported and comfortable, and believe that great communication is key in all transactions. To ensure all investors receive exceptional levels of communication and service, Ray White Bendigo have an agent speaking both Cantonese and Mandarin.

To maximise property prices for each vendor, the team prides itself on a consistent and well-planned approach to selling your valuable asset. They are the leading agency for auction clearance rates in the Bendigo region. Ray White Bendigo’s senior auctioneer is award winning, and he is passionate about getting the most for your property. The experienced auction team conducts auctions all around Victoria, specialising in in-room auctions that see up to 15 properties auctioned in a night.

For the best real estate advice, call Ray White Bendigo today.
name: Ray White Bendigo

description: Located on the roundabout of Rowan & Baker Streets, Wangaratta, we service you with all the products that Elders has to offer. Located in North East Victoria, the Rural City of Wangaratta is 235 kilometres north east of Melbourne and 647 kilometres south of Sydney on the Hume Freeway. Wangaratta is the municipality's largest urban centre, with approximately 18,000 residents. Everton, Glenrowan, Oxley, Milawa, Moyhu, Peechelba, Springhurst, Whitfield, Whorouly and Eldorado are some of the larger rural centres. The region is renowned for world class wineries, gourmet food, spectacular scenery, historic legends, cultural heritage and access to numerous State and National Parks. An extensive river system, which includes the Ovens and King Rivers, winds through the townships that dot the valleys and plains, meeting at Wangaratta. Families are well served by 21 primary schools, three secondary schools, one specialist school, one TAFE Institute and many childcare and kindergarten facilities. There is also a centre for continuing education. The municipality provides strong recreational, commercial, educational, tourism and health facilities, including a modern private hospital. It has diverse industry and economic stability and is the regional headquarters for several state government agencies.
name: Elders Real Estate Wangaratta

description:
Located just 120 kilometres (an easy 90 minute drive or train ride) north of Melbourne, Castlemaine is the heart of Victoria's historic goldfields and is now at the centre of a new gold rush of metropolitan buyers fleeing Melbourne in search of a more relaxed lifestyle without sacrificing the cultural attractions and quality of services the city provides. What can you find here? Clean fresh air, rolling farmland, historic architecture, safe leafy streets, internationally famous gardens, including the grand Botanical Garden, vineyards and wineries, art galleries, a wide range of restaurants (from the posh to the populist), golf courses and sporting facilities, heritage sites, thousands of acres of pristine bush filled with wildlife - and a lot of friendly people who love their area.
Unlike most of the regional centres in Australia that appeal to tourists, weekenders and holiday makers, Castlemaine is supported by strong local industry. This solid business base generates considerable prosperity, confidence and pride. It also gives the area an atmosphere of substance and authenticity. Add to these benefits efficient healthcare, education and transport facilities, and you have something unique - not just in Victoria but in all Australia and perhaps the world. A big claim for a small town. Put it to the test.

description:
Business brokers and advisers who specialise in helping business owners

 

This simple philosophy embodies everything we do at Rinnovate. From our coaching modules to our business sales directory, our buyer advocacy service to our business advice consultations.


Our commercial approach is all about increasing the value of your business – whether you want to sell it, grow it or simply increase your sales and profits.  There are very few business consulting or business broker firms that have such expertise and hands on experience assisting business owners to buy and sell. 

Our team brings three key aspects to the important process of the sale of a business:

Expertise: we have the in-house expertise to properly analyse and value a business prior to offering it for sale, and then to manage all aspects of the sale, including the purchaser’s due diligence process, a financier’s review process, and managing third party stakeholders such as franchisors and landlords.  We also screen the business to evaluate if it is ‘sale-ready’ and, if not, recommend exactly what you need to do to get it there.

Energy: we devote rigorous attention to follow-up of leads; we bring enthusiasm to the sale process; and we bring a determination to persist until we achieve a sale.

Ethics: we don’t just chase a quick sale to the detriment of our vendors; we won’t take on listings where something is “not quite right”; and we bring the highest standards of professional conduct to the business sale process. 


On behalf of our vendors, we prepare a detailed information and marketing presentation to provide to potential buyers. Our advertising and marketing activities are wide-ranging, including use of social media, other electronic and print media, and direct marketing.

We screen buyer enquiries prior to providing any information about a business, to ensure the potential buyer is a suitable candidate for the acquisition. Strict confidentiality procedures are in place for protection of sensitive vendor information. 

In summary, we manage the entire sale process for the vendor, providing them a seamless and hassle-free sale experience, while also providing guidance and assistance to prospective buyers throughout the transaction.
name: NAI Harcourts Rinnovate Business Brokers

description:
Choosing An Agency Is Tough... LetUs Convince You!

1. Save Up To 65% on Agent’s Fees

We believe the industry must accept a change in the way salespeople operate being an industry leader, Changing Places have introduced a “Fixed Fee” commission structure based on the general demographic of the buyer, and the level of effort and resources required to achieve the best possible outcome for our clients, not the dollar value of your property. Our unique business model allows us to reduce running costs without sacrificing our world-class service, therefore we choose to pass this saving onto our clients saving you up to 65% on typical agent’s fees.

2. Our Centralised Database

We are in constant communication with a vast number of qualified buyers each week. These buyers are entered into our centralized data management system can opt in to automatically advised of any new property listings that match their buying criteria. Unlike traditional agency networks, all of our Area Specialists have access to this national network of buyers, effectively allowing our salespeople to market your property on a national scale putting your property in front of more buyers each week.

More Buyers + Emotionally Connected + In Competition = Premium Price

3. Our National Network of Salespeople

We employ, train and support a National network of salespeople who are experts in their field and well networked within their territory. Our training is intense so we ensure each and every Area Specialist is fully equipped and capable to effectively manage the sale of your property.

4. Our Website

In today’s world over 85% of real estate business happens online. We provide a modern platform for buyers and sellers alike to obtain up-to-date information about the property market, industry trends and tips on buying and selling residential real estate. We are continually striving to push the limits of technology.

5. A Tailored Approach

We do not favour one sale method over another. The most effective method of sale can vary from suburb to suburb, state to state. It is our approach to act in the best interest of our clients and in too many cases a property is auctioned only to leave an owner ultimately disappointed. Our Experienced Area Specialists have an intimate knowledge of their marketplace and will submit their recommendations based on factual evidence and the individual needs of the property. Fact: Out of area and passive buyers are more likely to pay a premium price for a property!

6. Personal Service

In most real estate agencies, you start out with the Principal of the firm or a Senior Salesperson, however, you ultimately find the person who ends up handing your sale is far less experienced. With Changing Places, the Area Specialist is dedicated to your property from day one and stays with you right throughout the sale process.

7. Administration Support

By providing exceptional administration support to all of our Area Specialists we eliminate a large percentage of downtime allowing our salespeople to focus the majority of their energy on achieving the best result for our clients, spending more time working with potential buyers for your property.

8. Training & Development

We believe training is key to success – all our salespeople go through an initial induction program into our brand were we teach demonstrate how our unique philosophy and commission structure can help everyday sellers who are looking for a great real estate experience. In addition to this we provide access to ongoing training events and seminars to ensure our team are fully equipped with state-of-the-art tools, knowledge, and industry best practices ensuring the very best possible outcome can be achieved for our clients.
name: Changing Places Real Estate Consultants

The Roccisano tradition of service goes back to the year 1958 when Joe Roccisano commenced his career in Real Estate. In 1970 he hung his company’s shingle in Deakin Avenue and commenced work as Principal and Director of Roccisano Real Estate. The name Roccisano has become highly respected and regarded in the Real Estate profession and has progressively grown into one of the market leaders in North West Victoria. The company is now headed by Mr Tony Roccisano who has built on the solid foundation of the firm his late father founded and is responsible for the strong growth of the business in recent years.

From the days of servicing clients in an FJ Holden, through recessions and community disasters, the company, has handled property in almost every street of our city and is why nobody understands Mildura property better than Roccisano Real Estate.

Our staff here at Roccisano Property Group are amongst the most qualified and experienced in North West Victoria. All are considered top performers in the industry and is the reason why Roccisano Real Estate is no.1 in Mildura on sales per head. We have a strong mix of both male & female sales people.

Our unique strategies for finding buyers or tenants and marketing properties, combined with discipline and hard work, make out team of highly skilled consultants true professionals who are highly regarded within the industry and the community.

Loyalty amongst staff and directors has endured that a strong team spirit continues to grow and prosper which will ultimately produce the best possible results for our clients.

Our Director, Tony Roccisano, is a licenced agent and auctioneer and is the second generation of his family to carry on the real estate tradition. Tony is the son of the late Joe Roccisano and has been in the Real Estate business since 1958.

Frances Roccisano is also a director and heads the Property Investment Department.  Frances started her career in 1981 and has vast experience in all matters of property management.

John Roccisano is a solicitor and is an associated director of the company. John acts as a consultant and legal advisor to the firm. John Roccisano is also the son of the late Joe Roccisano.

We know that big is not always best. That’s why our mission is to provide the most professional service and strive for excellence at all times

- To blend modern techniques with traditional values of personal attention and detail

- To provide a full range of Real Estate and associated services to meet client’s needs

- To work at all times in the client’s best interest

- To provide clients with accurate information by keeping up to date with market trends and technology

- To place at the client’s disposal the vast strengths and advantages of the Professional’s national and international network.

The Roccisano philosophy is based on an old Japanese motto, “All of us are better than one of us”. The professional group with over 400 offices provides an excellent environment in which to source and develop leading marketing strategies which, when combined with local expertise, experience and teamwork, becomes an unbeatable MARKET FORCE.

With our combined resources we’ve taken services into new areas that are often talked about but never tried in the past.

At Roccisano Real Estate, you will personally deal with a member of our Sales team assigned to handle your property. Your personal consultant will have the combined backing of the entire professional network with thousands of collective years in Real Estate Experience.
name: Professionals Mildura

description:
Tierney Real Estate was built on a passion for property and the desire to provide practical advice across the real estate sector. Our drive and sheer determination comes from a strong commitment to what we do and where we live.


"We believe in our knowledge of the Mildura region and we want to help the city have a strong and promising future" - Frank Tierney
name: Tierney Real Estate

description:
Gordon Agencies is a self-developed – not purchased – family business dedicated to customer satisfaction.

The business started 9 years ago with Peter leaving his previous employment to fulfil the desire to begin his own business and develop a company according to the ideals he believed made a good organisation.

 

Gordon Agencies Pty Ltd as it is now provide services in the Livestock industry including the buying, selling, exchanging & auctioning of all livestock including cattle, sheep, lambs, pigs, goats etc. Also the selling, buying, exchanging, letting or taking on lease of or otherwise dealing with or disposing of any real estate or business. Other services provided include clearing sale auctioning and Gordon Agencies is also now in the beginning stages of water brokering providing services to those who require the precious resource.
name: Gordon Agencies

description:
In 1985, John G. King began building steel frame homes in Ballarat. His vision was to pioneer a new standard of home building, using exclusively Australian made TRUECORE® steel.

In our first year of operations 35 homes were delivered. Today, JG King Homes has grown to a business that proudly builds for over 1,000 families each year. With 10 offices all around Victoria, we’re trusted by families for timeless home designs and safe, strong, highly considered builds.

Despite the recognition and accolades JG King Homes has won over the years, seeing our customers enjoy their homes is still the biggest reward of all.

We are Victoria’s largest builder of steel frame homes, but as a family-owned company, JG King Homes understands the importance of building an unrivalled home.
name: JG King Homes

description:
Robinvale Euston has a thriving horticultural sector, with rich soils, sunny Mediterranean climate, and secure and abundant water supply. The area is suitable for growing and processing a diverse range of quality edible products. The principle production activity is fresh table grapes (harvest Jan- Apr) as well as large-scale production of wine grapes, citrus, almonds, olives, carrots, pistachios, avocados, barley, wheat, sheep and other vegetable crops. Visitors to the region can sample much of this delicious produce fresh from the farm gate, when in season. 

Export markets for the Robinvale Euston horticulture industry are increasing rapidly as the reputation for the region's quality produce grows. This economic boom has created opportunities for both employment and local business services. Robinvale Euston offers seasonal or full time employment options for those who would like to experience a working holiday, or a permanent change of lifestyle. 

Important information for all investors
A fresh approch will be available in late January 2003, the innovative way to invest in Real Estate with Elders Real Estate Robinvale.

Thinking of moving or looking for Investment opportunities "anywhere in Australia"Give Elders Real Estate Robinvale a call
name: ELDERS ROBINVALE

description:
Established in February 2012 by local real estate agent Danny Edebohls, Danny Edebohls Property Sales soon became a household name in the local real estate scene and is now well and truly a market leader in real estate sales in the local area.



Specializing solely in property sales only, we provide a professional sales service where both vendor and purchaser activity is conducted in a private, personal & confidential environment. A boutique property sales agency embracing the latest in modern technology with three "dynamic digital displays" partnered by the latest ultra modern "touch screen display" brings both our shop front to life and our vendors property to life with multiple photos per property, per display giving totally unrivaled maximum exposure to each property WE LIST FOR SALE.

A truly local team with extensive knowledge of the local real estate market. We thrive on the opportunity to market your property and help all of our vendors in their quest to achieve a premium price for their property.

Repeat and referral business has always been fundemental to the success of the Danny Edebohls Property Sales team. We're proud of the fact that our clients come back to us time and time again, as well as referring us to their family & friends.

In November 2017, Danny Edebohls Property Sales was awarded the "Most Improved Real Estate Office" at the Australasian Real Estate awards. In addition to the office award several of our sales team and administration staff were nominated finalists for individual awards for specific categories.

RateMyAgent -  "Agency of the Year 2017". 

Rate MyAgent - "Agency of the Year 2018"

November 2018 - "Sales Team Of The Year 2018" at the Australasian Real Estate Awards.

description:
ROSS MADDALUNO REAL ESTATE IS FINALLY HERE

Due to public demand Ross is now Ross Maddaluno Real Estate.

Many of you already know Ross's style of getting the sales and getting the buyers. Many of you already know that ROSS GETS RESULTS.

We the team at Ross Maddaluno Real Estate, succeed because we don't follow the stale tactics of others before us. Your properties are as individual as you are and we tailor our strategies to suit the needs of your property. This means you get the right buyer at the right price in the shortest amount of time.

With the opening of our new sales office in Tarwin Street Morwell, comes a new face, Alan Johnson. With 24 years real estate experience, he is a man with all the answers. Having negotiated the sales of country mansions in England and investment and family homes in the Dandenong area for many years, he brings a wealth of experience.

With the company's high profile and specialist marketing and Alan's top negotiating skills, all together to make a highly organised, competent and unique team.

If you want your properties to be managed effectively, if you want your properties sold in an average of three weeks at the market price, then you must give Ross or Alan a call.

Since opening Stockdale & Leggo Latrobe Valley Pty Ltd in Morwell in October 1999, it has become one of the most successful franchises of the Stockdale & Leggo 90 plus franchises throughout Victoria.

description:
About Us  
Latrobe First National Real Estate opened for business in September 2001 and boasts many years of real estate experience amongst its professional sales and property management team. Situated in the major provincial city of Traralgon, which is positioned on the Princes Highway 160kms east of Melbourne, it is well known for its power generation and paper manufacturing industries, but is also surrounded by rich grazing and dairying country. Traralgon boasts one of the best locations in Australia for accessibility to snowfields, high country, rainforests, National Parks, magnificent Gippsland Lakes, some of the best beaches in Australia, historic gold mining towns and Melbourne, all within a pleasant two hours drive. Latrobe First National was developed by a dedicated team of real estate professionals who saw a way to do it better, and offer you friendly and professional service that is second to none. With our high profile office in a location opposite the new Business Post Office, and our first class window display, you can be sure that when you choose Latrobe First National to market or manage your property you'll have the best real estate agency working for you.
name: First National Real Estate Latrobe

description:
With 80 years in the Real Estate industry, Keith Williams Real Estate in Traralgon have become the Company that families know and trust.  We know every market and challenge.

Established in 1941, Keith Williams Real Estate are now a 4th generation family business and continue to lead the strong Traralgon Real Estate market and surrounding areas in the Latrobe Valley.

Your Move is Our Move

description:
With almost 15 years’ experience in the Real Estate industry, Russell believes that honesty and integrity are non-negotiable when dealing with Property – whether it be Sales or Rentals.

“It’s easy to do the right thing. Honesty and openness is easy and uncomplicated” says Russell.
 
A social and outgoing person, Russell enjoys interaction of the industry and embraces the challenges that go along with it as well. With the approach of always doing what’s best for his clients, Russell says: “People may forget what you said but they will never forget how you made them feel”
Russell prides himself on providing exceptional service and follow up.

Enjoying travel to Asia, Russell is always planning for the future. Quality time spent with family & friends is also essential to Russell. He loves to cook and entertain so there’s always an extra setting at the dinner table!
 
Owning Real Estate Russell understands the importance of providing enjoyable and hassle free service.
After working in Real Estate in Lakes Entrance, Russell has enjoyed exploring the Latrobe Valley and all it has to offer and getting involved in the Community.
 
As the Principal of Latrobe Valley Real Estate, Russell is looking forward to building a team of great culture and professional service that goes that ‘extra mile’ for his clients.
 
“Our business plan is simple: To work with clients that are so happy with our service they refer us to their friends and family” Russell says.
name: Latrobe Valley Real Estate

description:
Ray White (Traralgon) Pty. Ltd., has been trading in the Traralgon Area since 1938, firstly as John McMahon & Co., and later as Ray White (Traralgon) Pty. Ltd., when the company joined the franchise group in 1987. 

Ray White (Traralgon) Pty. Ltd., specialises in the residential market of Traralgon City and surrounding areas.

Traralgon is one of Gippslands leading and progressive cities and is situated about 160 kilometres east of Melbourne. Population is around 22,800 including lovely surrounding rural areas. Traralgon is only 1 and a 1/2 hours drive from the snowfields of Gippsland Lakes.

Traralgon is generally considered to offer the best residential facilities in the area and is serviced by a well designed and thriving Central Business District. An excellent range of educational facilities, including public and private primary and secondary schools, with Monash University Gippsland Campus being 15 minutes drive to nearby Churchill
name: Ray White Traralgon
