The reputation of Hayden Real Estate Ocean Grove has been forged through professionalism, knowledge and service.
 
While the evolution has been exciting, the company is now a blend of some of the most successful real estate businesses on the Bellarine Peninsula.
 
During this journey the Hayden Real Estate team have strived to provide their customer base with exceptional knowledge and service. The Property Managers are an expert team; the Sales Consultants continue to produce market leading results; and administrative support team implements the systems to ensure nothing slips through the cracks, so that the needs of tenants and landlords, vendors and purchasers can be met and exceed.
name: Hayden Real Estate Ocean Grove

description:
Pavilion Property’s unique approach is centred around consistently delivering market-leading outcomes

After more than 50 years of combined experience across the many facets of the property industry, each Director brings a wealth of knowledge and a strong track record of delivering success for our clients to the business. Leveraging our extensive experience and strong networks, we’ve focused on bringing the most effective approaches together, to establish Pavilion Property.

Our business embraces innovation, striving to always stay a step ahead of this ever-changing, dynamic market.

Pavilion Property’s unique approach is centred around consistently delivering market- leading outcomes for clients.

 

WHAT'S IMPORTANT

Our Directors have truly 'seen it all'.  

Through our varied experiences, we have consciously identified that the way employees are treated was a key factor that influenced how they perform in the field.

“We believe that if our people want to work with us, they will perform at their best all the time; in turn providing the highest level of service to each of our clients,” says Joe Morabito, Director at Pavilion Property.

WHAT WE BELIEVE

Ongoing investment in professional development allows the Pavilion Property team to deliver the best possible results for our clients. We are committed to expanding our skill base via a comprehensive training program, ensuring that our people can provide industry-leading service and results.

Our Directors – Michael, Dan and Joe – are passionate about continuous mentoring and are always available to team members and clients to provide expert advice and guidance.

The Pavilion Property team has undertaken extensive training with trainers recognised internationally as some of the best in the field, across topics including sales, NLP, mentoring and management.

SERVICEABILITY

The real estate industry is driven by reputation.

At Pavilion Property, we believe that times are changing as clients come to expect more from their agents. Our mission is to build and maintain the strongest reputation in the markets that we serve.

We will always strive to achieve the best results for our clients, whilst maintaining our strength and integrity.

 

OUR MISSION

We are committed to exceeding your expectations.
name: Pavilion Property

description: RT Edgar strives to set innovative real estate results from our renowned range of services, with an emphasis on achieving optimum, tangible results. Represented by a dedicated team of professional property specialists, our reputation is the result of continued commitment to your individual needs married with absolute integrity. We are focussed and accountable – our return and referral business is testimony to this attitude. Whether buying or selling, our comprehensive knowledge of Melbourne’s inner city and premium locales will ensure RT Edgar achieve optimum results and maximum return from your investment
name: RT Edgar Ocean Grove

description:
This Company Profile might be about us, but we like to think it’s all about you.

Bellarine Property was born on the 1st of March 2011 & every member of our team has had a reputable career in the Real Estate industry at ‘household-name’ agencies. Property is an ever-changing market with the vicissitudes of house prices equalling that of a roller-coaster. We enjoy the ride, but we certainly don’t sit back and relax.

As professional estate agents, we are constantly researching and monitoring local and national property trends so we can deliver the most informed, the most complete and the best-executed sales techniques and marketing solutions.

Whether it’s an investment or a family home, people spend a lot of time and energy to ensure their property is working for them. Not only will we do the work and worry for you, but we’ll turn it into a pleasant and positive process and ultimately reward you with the most desirable outcome.

description:
Pavilion Property’s unique approach is centred around consistently delivering market-leading outcomes

After more than 50 years of combined experience across the many facets of the property industry, each Director brings a wealth of knowledge and a strong track record of delivering success for our clients to the business. Leveraging our extensive experience and strong networks, we’ve focused on bringing the most effective approaches together, to establish Pavilion Property.

Our business embraces innovation, striving to always stay a step ahead of this ever-changing, dynamic market.

Pavilion Property’s unique approach is centred around consistently delivering market- leading outcomes for clients.

 

WHAT'S IMPORTANT

Our Directors have truly 'seen it all'.  

Through our varied experiences, we have consciously identified that the way employees are treated was a key factor that influenced how they perform in the field.

“We believe that if our people want to work with us, they will perform at their best all the time; in turn providing the highest level of service to each of our clients,” says Joe Morabito, Director at Pavilion Property.

WHAT WE BELIEVE

Ongoing investment in professional development allows the Pavilion Property team to deliver the best possible results for our clients. We are committed to expanding our skill base via a comprehensive training program, ensuring that our people can provide industry-leading service and results.

Our Directors – Michael, Dan and Joe – are passionate about continuous mentoring and are always available to team members and clients to provide expert advice and guidance.

The Pavilion Property team has undertaken extensive training with trainers recognised internationally as some of the best in the field, across topics including sales, NLP, mentoring and management.

SERVICEABILITY

The real estate industry is driven by reputation.

At Pavilion Property, we believe that times are changing as clients come to expect more from their agents. Our mission is to build and maintain the strongest reputation in the markets that we serve.

We will always strive to achieve the best results for our clients, whilst maintaining our strength and integrity.

 

OUR MISSION

We are committed to exceeding your expectations.

description:
Gippsland Real Estate operates offices in Maffra and Heyfield to service these towns and the surrounding district.

The three directors of Gippsland Real Estate Pty Ltd boast a combined experience in excess of 60 years in the local real estate market and are all involved on a daily basis to provide personal service to our clientele.

We have five Licensed Estate Agents, three auctioneers, two dedicated rural agents, an experienced property management team and a dedicated support staff all offering our clienete prompt, polite and professional service. All Gippsland Real Estate staff are motivated, highly trained and qualified. The company has an emphasis on staff training and bringing a fresh and innovative approach to real estate services.

We specialise in all facets of real estate including:

  • House and land sales
  • Rural sales
  • Property Management
  • Commercial sales and leasing
  • Industrial land
  • Developments
  • Clearing Sales
  • Auctioneering
  • Irrigation Water Sales

We are members of the Real Estate Institute of Victoria and abide by its strict Code of Conduct and Professional Standards.

We are committed to providing superior customer service delivered professionally, with honesty and integrity and always in the best interest of our clients.

The team members at Gippsland Real Estate have a thorough knowledge of the Maffra and Heyfield townships and surrounding district and contribute to a wide range of community and sporting activities through personal involvement and/or company sponsorship

MAFFRA OFFICE
In the late 1950’s, Mr James R Hill opened a real estate office at 120 Johnson Street, Maffra. Although the business underwent a number of name changes and proprietorship, it has operated continuously at the same site, most recently as L J Hooker Maffra.

In the mid 1970’s, another well-known local identity Mr Norm Pentland commenced a separate business, trading as Norm Pentland Real Estate. Over the ensuring years, this business also underwent a number of changes until it was purchased in 2001 and continued operation as Maffra Town & Country Real Estate Pty. Ltd.

In July 2012, L J Hooker Maffra and Maffra Town & Country Real Estate merged to become Gippsland Real Estate Pty Ltd. The new business purchased the adjoining property to 120 Johnson Street, extensively renovated the site, and now operates from a higher visible, prominent and modern building offering our clients maximum exposure in the market place.

HEYFIELD OFFICE
An existing agency was purchased in 2004 and commenced operation as a franchise of LJ Hooker.
In August 2014, the operation of the business converted to Gippsland Real Estate. It continues to operate from its prominent corner location in Heyfield.
name: Gippsland Real Estate

description:
Business brokers and advisers who specialise in helping business owners

 

This simple philosophy embodies everything we do at Rinnovate. From our coaching modules to our business sales directory, our buyer advocacy service to our business advice consultations.


Our commercial approach is all about increasing the value of your business – whether you want to sell it, grow it or simply increase your sales and profits.  There are very few business consulting or business broker firms that have such expertise and hands on experience assisting business owners to buy and sell. 

Our team brings three key aspects to the important process of the sale of a business:

Expertise: we have the in-house expertise to properly analyse and value a business prior to offering it for sale, and then to manage all aspects of the sale, including the purchaser’s due diligence process, a financier’s review process, and managing third party stakeholders such as franchisors and landlords.  We also screen the business to evaluate if it is ‘sale-ready’ and, if not, recommend exactly what you need to do to get it there.

Energy: we devote rigorous attention to follow-up of leads; we bring enthusiasm to the sale process; and we bring a determination to persist until we achieve a sale.

Ethics: we don’t just chase a quick sale to the detriment of our vendors; we won’t take on listings where something is “not quite right”; and we bring the highest standards of professional conduct to the business sale process. 


On behalf of our vendors, we prepare a detailed information and marketing presentation to provide to potential buyers. Our advertising and marketing activities are wide-ranging, including use of social media, other electronic and print media, and direct marketing.

We screen buyer enquiries prior to providing any information about a business, to ensure the potential buyer is a suitable candidate for the acquisition. Strict confidentiality procedures are in place for protection of sensitive vendor information. 

In summary, we manage the entire sale process for the vendor, providing them a seamless and hassle-free sale experience, while also providing guidance and assistance to prospective buyers throughout the transaction.
name: NAI Harcourts Rinnovate Business Brokers

description:

description:
The question is, why not?

At Choice Group Real Estate, we don’t just look at your property as bricks and mortar we look at it as a home filled with memories, another chapter in your story. We see potential for another story to come and we want to help you get the most out of your property so you can live with no regrets.
We know selling a home can be a daunting task, but we want to take the fear out of selling by putting your mind at ease by knowing that we’re always doing what’s best for you. We also make it a simple process and will involve you every step of the way.
The last thing we want you to feel is left out of the process, that’s why communication is key here at Choice Group Real Estate we’ll give you regular updates of interest we’ve had in the property and we’ll communicate any updates. In saying that, it doesn’t mean you’ll be bombarded with texts or calls, if you only want to hear from us once a week then that’s what we’ll do (unless we’ve received an offer of course!)
We have many platforms where we can advertise your property, whether it’s a ‘Coming Soon’ or ‘For Sale’ sign out the front, or an eye catching advert on domain , we also advertise on social media so people can tag friends or family who might be interested in the property.
We’re selling your property because it’s what we LOVE to do! Our favourite part of the process is seeing the smile on your face when the SOLD sticker goes on. Whether it’s vacant land, a local unit, a family home or a property with plenty of land we’re here to help you all the way and we want you to close this chapter with no regrets.

First in the Swan Hill district

As co-principals of Ray White Swan Hill, Cameron Smits and Fiona Hawley have been leading agents in the district for a decade. Fiona, the first female real estate agency owner in the district, is breaking new ground for women in the industry.


Full-service real estate agency

Ray White Swan Hill offers the full gamut of property services, including home sales, property management and commercial property services in Swan Hill and nearby towns like Lake Boga and Murray Downs. Looking after around 50% of local sales and a substantial property management portfolio, we’ve developed a formidable team.


Fresh approach to Swan Hill real estate

Our acquisition of Wood & Co – a local real estate agency for 100+ years – not only helped us to boost our business, but also brought Brian Wood, the former owner, into our team for invaluable continuity.


Joining Ray White, a fourth-generation international brand with roots in regional Australia, our team now has access to advanced sales and property management processes and technology. Innovations such as 3D walkthroughs and digital campaign materials mean a more professional service; our properties stand out and reach more potential property buyers across Australia. 


Auctions: Upping the ante

With a more sophisticated auction process, and making it easier for buyers to fall in love with your property, we’re moving the needle on how properties are sold. Auctions are transparent for all, and work especially well for estate sales with several beneficiaries.


Our regional renaissance

A recent survey by the Regional Australia Institute (RAI) revealed that 1 in 5 city dwellers are considering a move to regional. The RAI ‘Move to More’ campaign highlights our affordable housing, job opportunities and wonderful community lifestyle. 


With Swan Hill property prices on the rise, we’re seeing sales by long-term property investors, opening the market to new buyers. If you’re looking for a forward-thinking real estate team, we’d love to chat!

Visitors to the region can sample much of this delicious produce fresh from the farm gate, when in season. 

Export markets for the Robinvale Euston horticulture industry are increasing rapidly as the reputation for the region's quality produce grows. description:
Business brokers and advisers who specialise in helping business owners

 

This simple philosophy embodies everything we do at Rinnovate. From our coaching modules to our business sales directory, our buyer advocacy service to our business advice consultations.


Our commercial approach is all about increasing the value of your business – whether you want to sell it, grow it or simply increase your sales and profits.  There are very few business consulting or business broker firms that have such expertise and hands on experience assisting business owners to buy and sell. 

Our team brings three key aspects to the important process of the sale of a business:

Expertise: we have the in-house expertise to properly analyse and value a business prior to offering it for sale, and then to manage all aspects of the sale, including the purchaser’s due diligence process, a financier’s review process, and managing third party stakeholders such as franchisors and landlords.  We also screen the business to evaluate if it is ‘sale-ready’ and, if not, recommend exactly what you need to do to get it there.

Energy: we devote rigorous attention to follow-up of leads; we bring enthusiasm to the sale process; and we bring a determination to persist until we achieve a sale.

Ethics: we don’t just chase a quick sale to the detriment of our vendors; we won’t take on listings where something is “not quite right”; and we bring the highest standards of professional conduct to the business sale process. 


On behalf of our vendors, we prepare a detailed information and marketing presentation to provide to potential buyers. Our advertising and marketing activities are wide-ranging, including use of social media, other electronic and print media, and direct marketing.

We screen buyer enquiries prior to providing any information about a business, to ensure the potential buyer is a suitable candidate for the acquisition. Strict confidentiality procedures are in place for protection of sensitive vendor information. 

In summary, we manage the entire sale process for the vendor, providing them a seamless and hassle-free sale experience, while also providing guidance and assistance to prospective buyers throughout the transaction.

description: Since moving to premises in the central Business District Wodonga Real Estate Best Agents has grown from a 5 person operation to one of Wodonga’s largest and most professional Real Estate Agencies. Now employing over 30 dedicated and professional people who cover all facets of Real Estate including Residential, Rural & Lifestyle Sales and Property Management, Commercial & Industrial sales and leasing. Our ultra modern offices are complemented by “up to the minute,” electronic data and communication systems that keep all personnel informed and as close as a phone call away from serving you. Wodonga Real Estate Best Agents prides itself on its service delivery with constant 24 hour access in both Real Estate Sales and Property Management which is beneficial to Sellers, Buyers, Landlords and Tenants alike. Our bright well lit premises are located in Stanley Street which has recently been redeveloped into a mall with eating houses that cater for “Al Fresco” dining, as well as providing places to sit and relax during a busy days shopping and admire the various ornamental trees sculptures and water features. The Mall is used constantly for outdoor entertainment and food shows and will one day be the Café-Restaurant centre of the rapidly maturing Wodonga. Wodonga Real Estate Best Agents strives to make Real Estate as stress free as possible. We trust you will enjoy browsing through our web site which is updated regularly and would welcome your enquiry.
name: Wodonga Real Estate Best Agents

description:
At Georgette Nehme Real Estate, Georgette Nehme and James Veneris bring together their differing yet complimentary backgrounds and areas of knowledge, expertise and experience in providing professional real estate services. We are a niche agency that can offer highly specialised real estate sales, property management and advocacy services.

 
Georgette brings her vast experience as a sales and marketing specialist after working for several years with a large national franchise whilst James compliments and enhances this with his financial, legal and taxation knowledge and expertise in property related transactions and holds a Master of Applied Finance qualification.
 
Combined, these two attributes provide the perfect receipe for a holistic approach towards delivering high quality real estate services. The agency has been operating since 2009 and is located in the CBD of Albury's largest and fastest growing suburb of Lavington, opposite the Lavington Post Office and the large Centro Lavington Shopping Centre and caters for all parts of Albury/Wodonga and surrounds.
name: Georgette Nehme Real Estate
